WEBVTT

00:55.666 --> 00:57.125
[announcer] Please pay
close attention

00:57.291 --> 00:59.333
to this important
announcement.

01:06.583 --> 01:08.583
[man breathing heavily]

01:23.833 --> 01:25.250
[whirring]

01:32.166 --> 01:34.166
[dramatic music
playing over video]

01:37.458 --> 01:40.583
[announcer] Millions of people
have been affected by crime.

01:43.375 --> 01:46.291
Civil unrest
was at an all-time high...

01:46.458 --> 01:48.541
and mass unemployment
and homelessness...

01:48.708 --> 01:51.083
drove Los Angeles
into a crime epidemic.

01:52.083 --> 01:54.208
Prisons were overcrowded...

01:55.208 --> 01:57.083
...citywide Red Zones
were established...

01:57.250 --> 01:58.500
to restrict individuals

01:58.666 --> 02:00.833
implicated
in violent activities...

02:03.333 --> 02:05.625
...and still, hundreds
of our heroes in blue...

02:05.791 --> 02:07.291
were killed
in the line of duty.

02:07.458 --> 02:10.208
Now, extreme circumstances
call for extreme measures.

02:10.375 --> 02:12.291
We need the Mercy Court...

02:12.458 --> 02:13.833
and I will be encouraging
my colleagues

02:14.000 --> 02:15.333
on both sides of the aisle...

02:15.500 --> 02:16.500
to support it.

02:17.916 --> 02:19.750
[narrator] After two years
in operation...

02:19.916 --> 02:21.458
this program is the reason

02:21.625 --> 02:23.250
you can sleep
peacefully at night.

02:24.166 --> 02:25.458
Violent capital offenders

02:25.625 --> 02:28.125
are now judged
by artificial intelligence...

02:28.291 --> 02:30.333
which reduces
the need for lengthy trials...

02:30.500 --> 02:32.416
by acting as judge...

02:32.583 --> 02:33.583
jury...

02:33.750 --> 02:35.000
and executioner.

02:35.166 --> 02:37.041
In this fully
autonomous courtroom...

02:37.208 --> 02:39.583
suspects
are presumed guilty...

02:39.750 --> 02:41.500
unless proven innocent.

02:42.750 --> 02:45.750
Mercy analyzes it all
with pinpoint precision...

02:45.916 --> 02:48.000
drawing on an immense
range of data...

02:48.166 --> 02:51.000
including evidence
provided by the LAPD...

02:51.166 --> 02:52.708
and its quadcopter team.

02:52.875 --> 02:54.416
Since launching
this program...

02:54.583 --> 02:57.083
Mercy has already
impartially judged...

02:57.250 --> 03:00.416
sentenced and executed
18 individuals...

03:01.916 --> 03:04.666
cutting crime
in the city by 68%...

03:04.833 --> 03:06.625
saving billions
of tax dollars...

03:06.791 --> 03:08.833
due to the accuracy
and efficiency

03:09.000 --> 03:10.083
of the program.

03:10.250 --> 03:12.791
Mercy uses hard facts
and a wealth of evidence...

03:12.958 --> 03:15.416
to ensure justice is served...

03:15.583 --> 03:18.375
within hours of a murder
being committed.

03:18.541 --> 03:20.416
It's the ultimate
crime deterrent.

03:20.583 --> 03:22.958
The freedoms that
all Americans cherish...

03:23.125 --> 03:24.541
are now protected by a system

03:24.708 --> 03:26.333
designed
to eliminate threats...

03:26.500 --> 03:28.291
-quickly and efficiently.
-[groans]

03:28.458 --> 03:31.458
The future of law enforcement
is Mercy...

03:32.125 --> 03:34.541
and you are its next case.

03:35.791 --> 03:37.250
To ensure a fair trial...

03:37.416 --> 03:38.416
you, the accused,

03:38.583 --> 03:40.708
will have access
to crime scene evidence...

03:40.875 --> 03:42.666
and your complete
digital footprint.

03:43.083 --> 03:44.166
[man] Holy shit.

03:44.333 --> 03:45.333
-Hey. Hey.
-You will have a chance

03:45.500 --> 03:46.500
to defend yourself...

03:46.666 --> 03:47.958
-How the hell did I get here?
-...but understand...

03:48.125 --> 03:50.666
Mercy does not make mistakes.

03:52.041 --> 03:53.041
Your city thanks you

03:53.208 --> 03:54.875
for participating
in the Mercy program.

03:55.041 --> 03:57.458
Your contribution will restore
peace and stability

03:57.625 --> 03:58.958
to our communities.

03:59.291 --> 04:00.875
Mercy is justice

04:01.041 --> 04:03.083
-for a better future.
-Get me out of this chair.

04:03.250 --> 04:04.250
You have been assigned

04:04.416 --> 04:05.875
-case number 19.
-[man] Hello?

04:06.041 --> 04:09.708
Hello!

04:12.500 --> 04:13.500
[music stops]

04:13.666 --> 04:15.250
This is
the Mercy Capital Court.

04:15.416 --> 04:16.416
I'm Judge Maddox.

04:16.583 --> 04:18.208
I will preside
over your trial today.

04:18.375 --> 04:20.833
[man] Wait. No, no, no.
What are you talking about?

04:21.000 --> 04:22.416
There is no trial.

04:23.041 --> 04:24.166
I'm Detective Raven.

04:24.333 --> 04:26.666
[Maddox] Please exhale
a deep breath.

04:26.833 --> 04:28.833
Hold on. Just wait a...
Wait a second.

04:29.250 --> 04:30.666
-Identity is confirmed.
-[Chris] Okay...

04:30.833 --> 04:32.458
[Maddox] Please exhale
a deep breath.

04:32.625 --> 04:34.416
I put eight people
in this chair.

04:34.583 --> 04:36.041
I'm Chris Raven
from robbery-homicide.

04:36.208 --> 04:37.208
I don't belong here.

04:37.375 --> 04:40.083
Please exhale, Mr. Raven.

04:41.375 --> 04:42.875
-[exhales sharply]
-[Maddox] Thank you.

04:43.041 --> 04:44.333
Your blood alcohol level

04:44.500 --> 04:46.125
has now reduced
sufficiently for trial.

04:46.291 --> 04:47.583
Wait. How long was I out?

04:47.750 --> 04:50.291
-5 hours, 26 minutes.
-Man.

04:50.458 --> 04:51.833
Before we proceed,
you must swear

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
that all testimony
you give this court...

04:54.166 --> 04:56.500
will be honest and truthful.

04:57.958 --> 04:58.958
Wait.

05:00.708 --> 05:01.708
Hold on. Just hold on.

05:01.875 --> 05:02.875
Wait a second.
This can't be real.

05:03.041 --> 05:05.166
I assure you,
this is very real.

05:05.333 --> 05:06.416
You must swear an oath.

05:06.583 --> 05:08.208
Look, if you think
that this is real...

05:08.375 --> 05:10.166
you are making
a very big mistake.

05:10.333 --> 05:11.791
[Maddox] And if there
is a mistake,

05:11.958 --> 05:13.041
I will uncover it...

05:13.208 --> 05:15.875
but you must comply
with the rules before I can.

05:16.041 --> 05:18.000
Okay, fine. Fine. I swear.

05:18.166 --> 05:19.375
[Maddox] What do you swear?

05:20.625 --> 05:23.333
Well, to tell
the damn truth, okay?

05:24.166 --> 05:25.166
And maybe you can tell me
what I'm supposed

05:25.333 --> 05:26.333
to be telling
the truth about...

05:26.500 --> 05:28.375
-because whatever it is...
-Christopher Raven,

05:28.541 --> 05:29.541
you're before
this court today...

05:29.708 --> 05:32.166
charged with the murder
of your wife.

05:32.333 --> 05:33.375
Nicole Raven.

05:33.541 --> 05:34.541
[tense music playing]

05:40.833 --> 05:42.625
-[officer 1 shouting]
-[tires screeching]

05:43.583 --> 05:45.125
-[paramedic] Where's the vic?
-[SWAT 1] In the kitchen.

05:45.291 --> 05:46.125
[SWAT 2] Over here!

05:47.583 --> 05:49.041
-[officer 2] We need a medic!
-What?

05:49.208 --> 05:50.166
[paramedic 2] Is anyone else
in here?

05:50.333 --> 05:52.250
[Britt] No. There's no one
else here. It's just me.

05:52.416 --> 05:53.500
[paramedic] Yeah,
we're comin' in hot.

05:53.666 --> 05:54.666
[Britt] There's no one here.
It's just my mom!

05:54.833 --> 05:56.000
-Yeah, are you all right?
-[Britt] Yeah...

05:56.166 --> 05:57.666
[paramedic] Paramedics
on scene.

05:57.833 --> 05:59.375
[Britt] I don't know
what happened to her!

05:59.541 --> 06:01.500
[paramedic] Female,
stab victim, suspect unknown.

06:01.666 --> 06:02.791
[paramedic 2] Ma'am,
you're gonna be okay.

06:02.958 --> 06:05.208
Try to stay as still
as possible. Okay?

06:06.000 --> 06:08.541
[Britt] Yeah, I'm trying.
Please help her!

06:08.708 --> 06:09.875
[officer 3] Who did this
to you?

06:10.666 --> 06:11.750
[Britt] Please help my mom.

06:11.916 --> 06:13.375
[officer 3] Who?

06:13.541 --> 06:14.666
[weakly] Chris.

06:14.833 --> 06:16.291
[Chris] That's impossible.

06:16.833 --> 06:17.833
Oh, my God.

06:18.000 --> 06:18.833
[Maddox] This court
will now present...

06:19.000 --> 06:20.000
an opening statement

06:20.166 --> 06:22.041
evidencing your extensive ties
to the victim.

06:22.250 --> 06:24.708
-Oh, my God! Oh, Jesus Christ!
-Culminating today...

06:24.875 --> 06:27.291
when you and you alone were
in the house with Nicole...

06:27.458 --> 06:29.750
at the time that
she was stabbed to death.

06:29.916 --> 06:31.208
[breathing heavily]
You're lying to me.

06:31.375 --> 06:33.041
I urge you
to check for yourself.

06:34.041 --> 06:36.333
Voice commands
and touch-sensitive controls

06:36.500 --> 06:37.541
are available to you.

06:40.625 --> 06:41.625
Okay.

06:44.166 --> 06:45.166
[Maddox] Mr. Raven...

06:45.333 --> 06:47.541
...voice commands
and touch-sensitive controls

06:47.708 --> 06:48.833
-are available to you.
-Just search...

06:49.000 --> 06:51.083
Can you search Nicole Raven?

07:04.208 --> 07:05.833
[reporter] LAPD Officer
Chris Raven...

07:06.000 --> 07:08.708
has been arrested today
for the murder of his wife.

07:08.875 --> 07:10.791
Raven and his partner,
Jaq Diallo...

07:10.958 --> 07:13.083
were early supporters
of the Mercy program...

07:13.250 --> 07:15.916
and were responsible
for arresting David Webb...

07:16.083 --> 07:17.750
and bringing
the murderer to trial...

07:17.916 --> 07:20.333
as the first participant
in the Mercy Court...

07:20.500 --> 07:21.875
just two years ago.

07:22.041 --> 07:23.875
I'm proud to have sent
the first suspect

07:24.041 --> 07:25.291
for trial here...

07:25.458 --> 07:27.708
and I will continue
to send more...

07:27.875 --> 07:29.375
until the message

07:29.541 --> 07:30.875
-is received.
-This is really incredible.

07:31.041 --> 07:33.625
One day he's sending people
to the Mercy Court...

07:33.791 --> 07:35.708
the next day, he's there.

07:36.833 --> 07:38.250
Mr. Raven, how do you plead?

07:40.916 --> 07:42.958
Mr. Raven, how do you plead?

07:45.083 --> 07:46.500
Not guilty.

07:46.666 --> 07:48.458
I'm not guilty.

07:48.625 --> 07:50.500
I can't be.
I wouldn't hurt her.

07:50.666 --> 07:51.791
[Maddox] Based
on available evidence...

07:51.958 --> 07:54.541
I have already judged your
probability of guilt to be...

07:54.708 --> 07:56.708
97.5%.

07:56.875 --> 07:59.000
-[exhales shakily]
-This is 17.5% above...

07:59.166 --> 08:02.583
the 80% threshold
to trigger a Mercy trial.

08:06.666 --> 08:09.291
This is the Los Angeles
Municipal Cloud.

08:09.458 --> 08:11.375
Every private citizen
and organization

08:11.541 --> 08:12.708
is mandated by law...

08:12.875 --> 08:15.000
to connect
their devices to it.

08:15.083 --> 08:17.041
[overlapping chatter
and laughter]

08:17.208 --> 08:19.625
[Maddox] I have full access
to the servers during trials.

08:20.708 --> 08:23.083
It is the foundation
of my ability

08:23.250 --> 08:24.625
to reach verdicts.

08:26.541 --> 08:28.208
You may use
any and all resources

08:28.375 --> 08:29.416
available to this court...

08:29.583 --> 08:32.000
to provide me with evidence
of your innocence.

08:32.166 --> 08:33.583
Should you be found guilty...

08:33.750 --> 08:36.125
you will be executed
in precisely...

08:36.291 --> 08:37.708
-90 minutes.
-[Chris] No.

08:37.875 --> 08:41.250
-Your trial will now commence.
-No, no, no.

08:42.416 --> 08:44.000
This is wrong.

08:44.166 --> 08:45.416
Everything is wrong!
You gotta shut this thing off!

08:45.583 --> 08:46.583
You know I cannot do that.

08:46.750 --> 08:48.750
AI Systems
are prohibited by law...

08:48.916 --> 08:51.833
from any direct involvement
in taking of a human life.

08:52.000 --> 08:53.250
The chair's on a closed system

08:53.416 --> 08:54.750
and I have
no control over it...

08:54.916 --> 08:56.916
but it will not deliver
the fatal sonic pulse...

08:57.083 --> 09:00.125
if I end the trial before
the time limit is reached.

09:00.291 --> 09:02.500
For that to happen,
your probability of guilt...

09:02.666 --> 09:05.750
must fall below
the 92% threshold...

09:05.916 --> 09:07.125
of reasonable doubt.

09:07.291 --> 09:09.833
I'm not a murderer,
I'm on your side.

09:10.000 --> 09:12.458
I'm on your side!
Do you remember David Webb?

09:12.625 --> 09:14.458
Do you remember David Webb?

09:14.625 --> 09:15.833
Who started this?
I started this!

09:16.000 --> 09:17.875
I know precisely who you are.

09:18.041 --> 09:19.291
I know everything
that you have done

09:19.458 --> 09:20.833
to serve this court,
and I thank you.

09:21.458 --> 09:22.875
-Okay. What?
-But what you have done

09:23.041 --> 09:24.666
in the past...
is no longer significant.

09:24.833 --> 09:28.500
Here, the facts alone
will hold you to account...

09:28.666 --> 09:31.083
or, perhaps, save you.

09:35.000 --> 09:38.583
You arrived at work
at 8:51 this morning...

09:38.750 --> 09:41.041
but you never
got out of your vehicle.

09:42.125 --> 09:45.416
Instead, you returned
to your home.

09:46.750 --> 09:47.958
-[knocking on door]
-[bell ringing]

09:53.708 --> 09:55.416
[Nicole] You need to walk away
from the house.

09:55.583 --> 09:56.583
I'm done.

09:56.750 --> 09:57.916
Open the door.

09:58.708 --> 10:00.291
I'm not opening the door.

10:00.458 --> 10:02.250
You can talk to me
through a lawyer.

10:02.833 --> 10:04.666
I have keys in the truck.

10:04.833 --> 10:06.250
I'm gonna go get my keys
and unlock the door.

10:06.416 --> 10:07.750
Why don't you just...

10:07.916 --> 10:09.791
-be a grown-up?
-Chris, do not do that.

10:09.958 --> 10:11.041
[camera thuds]

10:17.500 --> 10:18.708
[keys clinking]

10:19.666 --> 10:21.958
[Nicole] Do not come in here!
Get out of my house!

10:22.125 --> 10:23.291
-[door slams]
-Get out of my house!

10:24.250 --> 10:27.500
[Maddox] You spent 26 minutes
inside the house with Nicole.

10:30.541 --> 10:32.625
Your daughter returned
from a sleepover.

10:33.083 --> 10:34.083
Mom?

10:43.666 --> 10:44.666
[Britt screams]

10:45.333 --> 10:46.875
[Maddox] Crime scene
data confirms

10:47.041 --> 10:48.208
that around this same time...

10:48.375 --> 10:50.875
Nicole was stabbed
by a right-handed man...

10:51.041 --> 10:52.875
and the single stab wound
was so aggressive...

10:53.041 --> 10:54.833
that it chipped
a vertebra in her spine

10:55.000 --> 10:56.458
in addition
to piercing her liver...

10:56.625 --> 10:57.625
[Chris] No, no, no.

10:57.791 --> 10:59.375
...and severing
her mesenteric artery.

10:59.833 --> 11:01.875
-That's not me.
-You are right-handed.

11:02.041 --> 11:03.208
Traces of your wife's blood

11:03.375 --> 11:05.416
were found on the clothes
you wore today...

11:05.583 --> 11:06.666
and the traces are fresh.

11:06.833 --> 11:07.916
After leaving the house,

11:08.083 --> 11:09.541
you drove
to the Harbor Master Bar...

11:09.708 --> 11:11.000
and began drinking heavily.

11:11.166 --> 11:12.166
No. No!

11:12.791 --> 11:13.791
Are you thirsty?

11:16.083 --> 11:17.083
Yes.

11:17.250 --> 11:18.916
-Do you have a headache?
-Yes.

11:19.083 --> 11:20.208
Well, your dehydration
and headache...

11:20.375 --> 11:22.000
are the result
of your blood alcohol level

11:22.166 --> 11:23.875
being 0.16 at the time
of your arrest.

11:24.041 --> 11:25.583
No, no way. No.

11:25.750 --> 11:27.250
No, I don't go to bars!
I don't go to bars!

11:27.416 --> 11:28.625
-That's not possible!
-You were arrested...

11:28.791 --> 11:30.250
at the Harbor Master Bar at...

11:30.416 --> 11:32.625
You're lying. You're lying.

11:32.791 --> 11:34.541
I do not lie...

11:34.708 --> 11:36.625
nor do the facts.

11:40.875 --> 11:42.541
[man] Yeah, Officer.
That's the guy.

11:42.708 --> 11:44.250
[soft rock music playing
over speakers]

11:45.375 --> 11:47.458
[Jacobs] Hey, Chris.
Everything okay here?

11:49.708 --> 11:51.250
[Beech] Detective,
we need to go.

11:51.416 --> 11:53.416
Nah. I think I'll stay here
and have another drink.

11:53.583 --> 11:55.458
-[Jacobs] You've had enough.
-[Beech] Let's go!

11:56.708 --> 11:57.708
[Chris grunting] Get off me!

11:59.291 --> 12:00.500
-[Chris grunts]
-[people screaming]

12:01.250 --> 12:02.875
[all clamoring]

12:06.125 --> 12:07.375
-[Jacobs] Hey, just what...
-[Taser crackling]

12:07.541 --> 12:08.541
[Chris screaming]

12:14.125 --> 12:15.708
[Chris grunting]

12:17.791 --> 12:18.791
Back the fuck up!

12:18.958 --> 12:20.416
[Jacobs] Chris, stop.
Don't do this.

12:20.583 --> 12:22.125
Okay. Okay.

12:24.958 --> 12:25.958
[Chris] Shit!

12:26.666 --> 12:28.083
[Jacobs] Hey, you! No! Stop!

12:28.541 --> 12:30.375
[officer 1] Come on, Chris.
That's enough.

12:31.333 --> 12:32.333
Hey, get him. Get him!

12:35.666 --> 12:36.833
-You, stop!
-[woman] Hey, hey!

12:37.000 --> 12:38.083
-Get out.
-[woman] What are you...

12:38.250 --> 12:39.666
Get off! Let him go.

12:39.833 --> 12:41.541
[man] My God! Leave me alone!

12:41.708 --> 12:43.291
[officer 1] Stop this, Chris!
Stop running!

12:43.458 --> 12:44.458
[Chris] If you don't
get outta the...

12:44.625 --> 12:45.500
[Chris grunts]

12:46.416 --> 12:47.416
[officer 2] Turn him over.

12:49.500 --> 12:51.416
Well, it is possible that
the excessive alcohol

12:51.583 --> 12:52.916
that you consumed...

12:53.083 --> 12:55.291
and the blow to your head,
may have impaired your recall.

12:55.458 --> 12:56.458
I don't remember the...

12:56.625 --> 12:58.166
I don't remember the bar.
I don't remember.

12:58.333 --> 13:00.000
[Maddox] I mean to say that
you may simply not remember

13:00.166 --> 13:01.625
killing your wife.

13:02.250 --> 13:03.250
[officer 2] Pick him up, guys.

13:03.416 --> 13:04.416
[officer 1] On his back.
Calling it in.

13:04.583 --> 13:06.458
Or you could be the one
who is lying.

13:07.000 --> 13:08.333
I have learned one constant

13:08.500 --> 13:09.500
in this court
and that is that...

13:10.333 --> 13:12.291
everyone lies.

13:12.458 --> 13:14.125
Why did you return home?

13:14.291 --> 13:15.708
I didn't. I don't...

13:15.875 --> 13:17.458
I don't remember anything!
Why don't...

13:17.625 --> 13:18.708
I gotta get outta here.

13:18.875 --> 13:19.916
And there's only one way
to do that...

13:20.083 --> 13:21.291
-so please focus.
-Get me outta here!

13:21.458 --> 13:22.708
Did you argue?

13:22.875 --> 13:25.125
About your drinking
or about your daughter?

13:25.291 --> 13:26.791
Oh, God. Britt.

13:27.625 --> 13:29.208
[grunts] Let me talk to her.
I need to talk to her.

13:29.375 --> 13:30.375
Unless they are a witness
to the act...

13:30.541 --> 13:31.541
of a crime being committed...

13:31.708 --> 13:32.916
juveniles are excluded...

13:33.083 --> 13:34.791
-from the Mercy trials.
-Okay, she's my little girl.

13:34.958 --> 13:35.958
-My...
-You are, however,

13:36.125 --> 13:38.250
free to review your daughter's
statement... if you wish.

13:38.416 --> 13:39.541
Her mom is dead
and she needs me.

13:39.708 --> 13:40.875
She is with
your late wife's parents.

13:41.041 --> 13:43.541
I want... to talk...

13:43.708 --> 13:45.125
to my daughter!

13:48.125 --> 13:50.500
I want my personal call.
Now. Right now.

13:52.291 --> 13:54.625
You may send
a request for a call.

13:56.166 --> 13:57.583
The rules
of this court stipulate...

13:57.750 --> 14:00.166
that if the deceased
was known to a person...

14:00.333 --> 14:01.750
there must be
a written request

14:01.916 --> 14:03.416
to contact them
in time of grieving.

14:03.583 --> 14:05.291
So, you may dictate one.

14:05.458 --> 14:06.500
Okay. Okay.

14:08.625 --> 14:10.666
You may dictate one now,
Mr. Raven.

14:10.833 --> 14:12.916
I heard you... the first time.

14:17.833 --> 14:20.958
Hey, Britt,
I need to talk to you.

14:21.125 --> 14:22.125
Uh...

14:23.250 --> 14:25.458
I know you'll be hearing
bad things about me...

14:25.625 --> 14:27.083
but they're not true.

14:27.250 --> 14:28.875
Just... uh...

14:33.833 --> 14:35.541
Just strictly...
Delete, delete, delete.

14:36.125 --> 14:37.916
Start over. [clears throat]

14:43.250 --> 14:44.291
Hey, kiddo.
[chuckles nervously]

14:45.000 --> 14:46.958
I did not hurt your mom.

14:47.125 --> 14:48.125
I would never...

14:48.291 --> 14:50.041
Delete it. Delete it.

14:51.583 --> 14:52.916
Shit.

14:53.500 --> 14:55.083
Perhaps I should
send an automated request

14:55.250 --> 14:56.916
without a personal message.

14:57.625 --> 14:58.916
Yeah. Yeah, do that.

14:59.916 --> 15:01.625
Generic request has been sent.

15:02.833 --> 15:03.833
[sighs]

15:04.000 --> 15:06.000
Despite the severity
of your alleged crime...

15:06.166 --> 15:09.000
this court mandates that you
must have an opportunity...

15:09.166 --> 15:10.625
to speak with your sponsor...

15:10.791 --> 15:13.541
and you will do so
before we proceed any further.

15:14.791 --> 15:15.791
[Rob] Oh yeah.

15:17.000 --> 15:18.083
-[Chris] Rob.
-Chris, hey.

15:18.250 --> 15:19.250
Rob, I don't remember.

15:19.416 --> 15:21.166
-I don't remember anything.
-Chris, stop, stop, stop.

15:21.333 --> 15:22.125
I don't remember
what happened.

15:22.291 --> 15:23.125
Look...

15:23.291 --> 15:27.125
they want me to stick
to the AA stuff, so...

15:27.291 --> 15:28.375
You just...

15:29.333 --> 15:31.125
You're supposed
to call me, man.

15:31.291 --> 15:32.333
If you're thinking about...

15:32.500 --> 15:33.791
If you're even
thinking about drinking.

15:33.958 --> 15:35.375
-Okay, it doesn't matter, Rob.
-You're supposed to call me.

15:35.541 --> 15:36.541
It doesn't.

15:36.666 --> 15:37.708
-It doesn't matter.
-So, what...

15:37.875 --> 15:39.750
-Brother, Nic...
-Chris.

15:41.166 --> 15:42.375
[Rob sighs]

15:44.125 --> 15:46.375
When she didn't show up
for her shift this morning...

15:46.541 --> 15:47.541
I just...

15:48.500 --> 15:52.041
I called the depot
as soon as I heard.

15:52.208 --> 15:53.791
Everybody here is...

15:55.083 --> 15:56.708
real messed up
about this, man.

15:56.875 --> 15:58.291
I could not have
hurt her, dude.

15:58.458 --> 15:59.625
I swear to God.

15:59.791 --> 16:02.416
You know, Chris,
I believe in karma. So...

16:03.000 --> 16:04.541
no matter what...

16:04.708 --> 16:05.708
you have...

16:06.375 --> 16:07.916
or haven't done...

16:08.083 --> 16:10.750
she's either gonna be
your best friend today...

16:10.916 --> 16:13.458
or the worst bitch
you ever met.

16:13.625 --> 16:14.791
Thank you, Mr. Nelson,
that's all the court

16:14.958 --> 16:16.375
-requires from you.
-Wait. Hold up.

16:16.541 --> 16:17.875
-Wait, wait, wait, I...
-Hey, can you hear me?

16:18.041 --> 16:19.041
Wait...

16:20.541 --> 16:21.541
Where did he go?

16:21.708 --> 16:22.958
Mr. Nelson
was only made available

16:23.125 --> 16:24.458
to address your relapse.

16:24.625 --> 16:26.375
You chose not to avail
of his support.

16:26.541 --> 16:29.333
He knows me,
he knows Nic, okay?

16:29.500 --> 16:31.500
Get him back on.
Get him back on, please.

16:31.666 --> 16:33.791
He'll... I mean, he'll tell
you that Nic and I were happy.

16:33.958 --> 16:34.958
I'm already acquainted

16:35.125 --> 16:36.250
with the state
of your marriage.

16:37.083 --> 16:38.333
What's that supposed to mean?

16:40.083 --> 16:42.875
You began dating Nicole Martin
20 years ago.

16:43.041 --> 16:44.583
After three years,
you were married

16:44.750 --> 16:46.583
in a ceremony
on Redondo Beach.

16:46.750 --> 16:49.083
You know, Chris has always
been the best man that I know.

16:50.875 --> 16:52.083
And then Nicole came along...

16:52.250 --> 16:54.583
and somehow she made
Chris even better.

16:54.750 --> 16:56.416
-To Chris and Nicole!
-[guests cheering]

16:59.250 --> 17:00.375
Ready or not...

17:03.041 --> 17:04.166
it's gonna be a boy.

17:05.000 --> 17:06.083
I gotta say, guys,
I know she's a girl...

17:06.250 --> 17:07.333
but Ray is a strong name.

17:07.500 --> 17:08.500
-[baby crying]
-Nah.

17:08.666 --> 17:09.916
[Maddox] Your daughter,
Britt Raven,

17:10.083 --> 17:11.250
was born one year later.

17:11.416 --> 17:15.208
And here we have the new
beautiful family Raven.

17:15.375 --> 17:16.625
I'm your Uncle Ray.

17:16.791 --> 17:18.083
That's Uncle Jimmy.

17:18.250 --> 17:19.250
[drone whirring]

17:23.333 --> 17:25.250
[Maddox] Your home life
was stable...

17:26.083 --> 17:27.750
until you endured
a traumatic incident

17:27.916 --> 17:29.541
in the line of duty.

17:30.791 --> 17:33.250
[Nicole] What happened?
What happened?

17:33.416 --> 17:34.416
What happened, baby?

17:34.583 --> 17:36.458
-Ray's dead.
-What? Baby, I'm so...

17:36.625 --> 17:37.708
[Maddox] And your
partner's death

17:37.875 --> 17:39.041
would upend everything...

17:39.208 --> 17:40.208
-for you and for your family.
-I just need you to say

17:40.375 --> 17:41.375
where you are.

17:41.541 --> 17:42.541
I've been worried about you,
and now I'm worried...

17:42.708 --> 17:43.708
What's so important
you had to call me then?

17:43.875 --> 17:44.833
...that this shows
you're clearly drunk.

17:45.000 --> 17:46.416
I mean, you know I was banking
on the lieutenant's spot...

17:46.583 --> 17:47.666
-to pay for it.
-Britt needs her own space.

17:47.833 --> 17:49.583
You've been promising it
for months.

17:50.208 --> 17:52.083
It's a basement.
All it needs is drywall.

17:52.250 --> 17:54.208
I just didn't think
I'd be a divorced mommy.

17:54.375 --> 17:56.166
All right.
That's enough. Stop!

17:56.250 --> 17:57.500
-Stop it!
-It's very hard.

17:57.666 --> 17:58.750
That's her personal shit.

17:58.916 --> 18:00.833
[Maddox] Nicole detailed
you losing your temper...

18:01.000 --> 18:02.875
57 separate times...

18:03.041 --> 18:06.166
in messages and calls
with her family and friends...

18:06.333 --> 18:08.291
...over the past
six months alone.

18:09.000 --> 18:09.916
Nonetheless,
the words of your family

18:10.083 --> 18:12.125
indicate that your marriage...

18:12.291 --> 18:14.666
...was straining from
your outbursts of anger...

18:14.833 --> 18:17.208
...and Nicole
was considering divorce.

18:17.833 --> 18:18.833
I loved my wife.

18:19.000 --> 18:20.958
Well, what human beings
experience as love...

18:21.125 --> 18:23.291
is merely a neurobiological
phenomenon...

18:23.458 --> 18:24.958
characterized
by the release of...

18:25.125 --> 18:27.750
dopamine, oxytocin,
and serotonin.

18:28.625 --> 18:29.625
Anger is also

18:29.791 --> 18:30.875
a neurobiological
phenomenon...

18:31.041 --> 18:33.125
and it can readily
overwhelm affection.

18:33.291 --> 18:34.291
-Sorry. Do you have a point?
-Well, the fact that

18:34.458 --> 18:36.125
you may have loved Nicole...
does not prohibit

18:36.291 --> 18:37.500
-the possibility...
-There you go!

18:37.666 --> 18:38.375
...that you lost
your temper...

18:38.541 --> 18:39.250
Just let me do it
how I wanna do it.

18:39.416 --> 18:41.083
No, because you're screwing
it up like you always do.

18:41.250 --> 18:43.791
-Jesus damn Christ! Chris.
-[Maddox] ...and murdered her.

18:44.750 --> 18:46.750
Whether you remember
doing so or not.

18:46.916 --> 18:48.125
[Chris] Nic, get back here.

18:48.291 --> 18:49.375
Come on, sweetheart. Let's go.

18:49.541 --> 18:50.500
[Britt] Sorry, Mom.
Are you all right?

18:50.666 --> 18:52.375
-[Chris] Nic!
-[Nicole] Jesus Christ.

18:54.000 --> 18:55.833
I can be a little fiery.

18:56.000 --> 18:57.541
That's a family trait. Okay?

18:57.708 --> 18:59.625
It doesn't mean
that I killed...

18:59.791 --> 19:01.041
[Britt] Mom's
in her bed crying.

19:01.208 --> 19:03.041
Dad legit scared the shit
out of us yesterday.

19:03.208 --> 19:04.458
Telling you, dude's dangerous.

19:04.625 --> 19:06.541
I can come get you
outta there if you want.

19:07.500 --> 19:09.166
You know,
I can make that happen.

19:09.333 --> 19:10.708
[Chris] Who the hell
is this guy?

19:11.750 --> 19:14.541
I mean, it's not like
your mom could stop me.

19:17.208 --> 19:18.208
Yeah, maybe.

19:18.791 --> 19:19.625
I heard my mom
talk to her friend

19:19.791 --> 19:20.583
about getting a divorce.

19:20.750 --> 19:22.583
Really hope
she meant that shit.

19:25.708 --> 19:26.666
Shit, you hear that?

19:26.833 --> 19:28.125
I think my dad's home.
I'm out.

19:28.291 --> 19:29.541
[sleazebag] Hey, wait.

19:29.708 --> 19:30.541
[Chris] What the hell
was that?

19:30.708 --> 19:32.583
We follow Britt's socials,
okay?

19:32.750 --> 19:34.041
She didn't post
any of this stuff.

19:36.625 --> 19:39.416
[Maddox] Your daughter has
two active Instagram accounts.

19:40.000 --> 19:42.416
It appears that she kept
this one from you...

19:42.583 --> 19:44.750
along with several
other online profiles...

19:45.541 --> 19:46.500
...but they're all linked

19:46.666 --> 19:48.583
to her cell phone
on the municipal cloud.

19:48.750 --> 19:49.750
[Chris] Jesus.

19:50.708 --> 19:53.291
For crying out loud,
she's 16 years old.

19:54.833 --> 19:56.625
This isn't Britt.

19:56.791 --> 19:57.875
[Britt] This shit is haunted.

19:58.750 --> 20:00.250
I mean,
it's a freaking ghost haunt...

20:00.416 --> 20:02.500
or I'm ripped off my tits.

20:02.666 --> 20:04.166
Call Zak Bagans, guys.

20:04.333 --> 20:05.458
[device chiming]

20:05.625 --> 20:07.250
Your daughter has accepted
a request to speak.

20:14.375 --> 20:15.708
Hey. Hey, kiddo.

20:16.208 --> 20:17.458
[Britt sniffles, sobs]

20:17.625 --> 20:18.875
[Britt] Mom's dead.

20:19.833 --> 20:21.166
I know.

20:21.333 --> 20:23.125
God, there was so much
blood and...

20:23.291 --> 20:24.416
I mean, I tried to stop it.

20:24.583 --> 20:25.750
I knew not to take
the knife out...

20:25.916 --> 20:26.708
because you always
told me that...

20:26.875 --> 20:28.083
-Hey, hey...
-...but it didn't work

20:28.250 --> 20:29.333
-and she died, Dad.
-You did everything right.

20:29.500 --> 20:31.000
-She just died.
-Listen, I... You did...

20:31.166 --> 20:32.125
You did everything right,
okay?

20:32.291 --> 20:33.291
And she knows it.

20:33.458 --> 20:35.625
-Your mother knows it.
-But it didn't work!

20:38.333 --> 20:39.833
Why are you there?

20:40.000 --> 20:40.958
I mean, why do they think
you killed her?

20:41.125 --> 20:42.083
You were at work, right?

20:42.250 --> 20:43.250
Why would they think
you did it?

20:43.416 --> 20:44.791
They made a mistake.

20:44.958 --> 20:46.666
Okay? That's all.
That's all this is.

20:46.833 --> 20:49.500
It's a big misunderstanding.

20:49.666 --> 20:50.791
Grandpa says
you don't get the Mercy trial

20:50.958 --> 20:51.958
unless you're guilty.

20:52.125 --> 20:54.208
Don't... listen
to your grandfather, okay?

20:54.375 --> 20:56.625
I know how this works,
and mistakes do happen.

20:57.333 --> 20:58.791
And that's all this is, okay?

20:58.958 --> 21:00.666
-Then come home.
-It's a mistake.

21:01.166 --> 21:03.583
Okay. Please just come home.

21:03.750 --> 21:05.708
I will as soon
as I clear this up.

21:05.875 --> 21:07.166
[Jeff] Britt, you sure
you wanna talk to him?

21:07.333 --> 21:08.333
Your father is there
for a reason.

21:08.500 --> 21:09.416
[Britt] Please come back.

21:09.583 --> 21:10.583
-[Jeff] Leave her be, Chris.
-I will, Britt.

21:10.750 --> 21:12.750
Okay, Jeff,
can you back off for a moment?

21:12.916 --> 21:14.708
Britt, listen to me, okay?
Listen to me.

21:14.875 --> 21:15.875
[Jeff] Britt,
give me the phone.

21:16.041 --> 21:16.958
[Chris] Whatever
happens today,

21:17.125 --> 21:17.958
I need you to know...

21:18.125 --> 21:20.708
that I did not
hurt your mom, okay?

21:20.875 --> 21:21.875
-I couldn't.
-[Jeff] Britt, listen to me.

21:22.041 --> 21:22.875
So, you gotta promise me

21:23.041 --> 21:23.958
you're always
gonna remember that...

21:24.125 --> 21:25.375
and promise me...

21:25.541 --> 21:26.666
-no matter what happens...
-[Jeff] That's enough.

21:26.833 --> 21:28.791
[Chris] Jeff, Jeff.
Britt. Hey, Britt!

21:29.708 --> 21:30.916
God!

21:31.083 --> 21:32.458
Oh, he's such an asshole.

21:32.625 --> 21:34.000
And that will count
as your call.

21:34.166 --> 21:35.166
[Chris scoffs]

21:35.666 --> 21:36.916
Why did she have
to be with them?

21:37.083 --> 21:38.250
Pending the outcome
of the trial...

21:38.416 --> 21:39.500
your late wife's parents

21:39.666 --> 21:40.958
are now her closest
living relatives.

21:41.125 --> 21:43.125
Did you hear
what he was saying to her?

21:44.000 --> 21:46.000
He's trying to turn her
against me.

21:46.958 --> 21:48.666
I was never
good enough for Nic.

21:48.833 --> 21:50.958
Mr. Raven, this is not
progressing your case.

21:51.125 --> 21:52.791
I must remind you
that the clock is ticking.

21:52.958 --> 21:54.125
'Cause they'd only
approve Mercy...

21:54.291 --> 21:57.125
if it looked like people
had an opportunity...

21:57.291 --> 21:58.416
to defend themselves!

22:01.083 --> 22:03.416
You and I both know
that this clock...

22:03.583 --> 22:04.666
is bullshit.

22:05.750 --> 22:06.750
You make your decisions

22:06.916 --> 22:08.833
about the people
in this courtroom...

22:09.458 --> 22:11.458
before they're even
in this chair.

22:12.458 --> 22:13.500
[Chris sniffles]

22:14.666 --> 22:15.875
I'm fucked.

22:16.500 --> 22:18.375
Anger is not helpful to you.

22:18.541 --> 22:20.458
Jesus Christ.
Okay, my wife is dead...

22:20.625 --> 22:22.458
and my daughter's been told
that I killed her, okay?

22:22.625 --> 22:24.916
So, yeah, maybe I need
a minute. All right?

22:25.083 --> 22:26.833
Do you understand that?
Do you?

22:27.000 --> 22:29.000
I was not designed to feel.

22:29.166 --> 22:31.125
My job is to assess the facts.

22:31.291 --> 22:33.208
So, no, I do not understand...

22:33.375 --> 22:34.958
-but I comprehend.
-Oh...

22:35.125 --> 22:36.833
You comprehend. That's...

22:39.166 --> 22:41.958
Well, that's great.
Okay. You comprehend.

22:43.208 --> 22:44.750
Hell of a bedside manner
you have there.

22:44.916 --> 22:45.916
I also comprehend that

22:46.083 --> 22:47.208
you're being distracted
by emotions...

22:47.375 --> 22:48.791
and you have
one hour and eight minutes...

22:48.958 --> 22:51.083
to reduce
your guilt probability by...

22:51.250 --> 22:53.208
5.5%.

22:53.375 --> 22:56.166
If you are innocent,
prove it to me.

22:57.250 --> 22:59.791
Otherwise, Britt will lose
both of her parents today.

23:04.208 --> 23:06.166
[sniffles] Okay.

23:11.958 --> 23:13.041
[grunts, exhales]

23:15.375 --> 23:16.458
[mumbles indistinctly]

23:19.916 --> 23:20.958
[Maddox] Mr. Raven.

23:21.125 --> 23:22.125
Okay.

23:24.041 --> 23:25.208
I need my partner.

23:26.333 --> 23:27.375
Give me Jaq.

23:27.875 --> 23:29.291
You may contact
whoever you wish

23:29.458 --> 23:30.958
at any point
during your trial...

23:31.125 --> 23:33.291
providing your purpose
is to gather evidence...

23:33.458 --> 23:35.708
or ask that they provide
character testimony.

23:35.875 --> 23:36.958
-Which one is it?
-Okay.

23:37.125 --> 23:38.166
I wanna to talk to my partner.

23:38.333 --> 23:39.375
-Which one is it?
-The second one,

23:39.541 --> 23:41.416
character stuff.
Jaq knows me and Nic.

23:42.125 --> 23:43.416
[device chiming]

23:45.833 --> 23:47.458
[indistinct police
radio chatter]

23:51.208 --> 23:52.625
-[Jaq] Yeah, hello.
-[Maddox] Detective Diallo...

23:52.791 --> 23:54.458
you're speaking
to the Mercy Court chamber...

23:54.625 --> 23:56.083
where Christopher Raven
is standing trial

23:56.250 --> 23:57.541
for his wife's murder.

23:57.708 --> 23:59.666
I know, I know. They told me.

23:59.833 --> 24:00.958
Chris, you're in
a hell of a mess, man.

24:01.125 --> 24:02.666
Jaq, I couldn't
have done this.

24:02.833 --> 24:04.541
You gotta believe me. I...

24:05.625 --> 24:07.916
Wait. Who was first on scene?

24:08.083 --> 24:10.250
[Jaq] Uh... Air unit.
Hey, am I clear to enter?

24:10.416 --> 24:12.166
[paramedic] Yeah. Go right in.

24:12.333 --> 24:13.833
-[Jaq] I'm inside.
-Good, good.

24:14.750 --> 24:15.958
I need us to walk the scene.

24:17.791 --> 24:18.791
Jaq, come on.

24:19.916 --> 24:21.166
Hey, listen, Chris.

24:21.833 --> 24:22.833
-Jaq, show me what...
-Mr. Raven,

24:23.000 --> 24:23.750
what are you doing?

24:23.916 --> 24:24.666
You must present
evidence or...

24:24.833 --> 24:25.958
I'm looking for evidence,

24:26.125 --> 24:27.083
and I'll present it
as soon as I find it.

24:27.250 --> 24:29.000
I need the crime scene files.

24:34.250 --> 24:35.291
All right, Jaq, come on,

24:35.458 --> 24:36.708
-let's walk it.
-Hey, listen, Chris...

24:37.500 --> 24:39.375
we need to get something
really clear here first.

24:39.541 --> 24:41.000
You know I'm down for this...

24:41.166 --> 24:42.416
but if it ends up
looking bad for you...

24:42.583 --> 24:45.083
that's exactly how I'm gonna
say it looks, okay?

24:45.250 --> 24:47.708
You know, we need every Mercy
trial to send a message...

24:47.875 --> 24:48.958
and if that message today

24:49.125 --> 24:50.833
is that cops
aren't above the law...

24:51.541 --> 24:53.458
I won't like it,
but I'll sleep good tonight.

24:53.625 --> 24:56.000
Nobody's more important
than that court.

24:56.166 --> 24:57.666
-Fair enough.
-[Maddox] Detective Diallo,

24:57.833 --> 24:59.041
you may proceed.

24:59.208 --> 25:00.541
Okay, then.

25:00.708 --> 25:01.958
Let's walk it.

25:02.125 --> 25:04.083
[Chris] Can I see
the scene scans, please?

25:07.375 --> 25:08.375
Your Honor.

25:08.541 --> 25:09.708
There you go.

25:13.791 --> 25:16.000
Now rendering
immersive reconstruction...

25:16.166 --> 25:18.208
based on available footage.

25:24.625 --> 25:25.625
[Chris] Can you
zoom in on that?

25:25.791 --> 25:26.875
Give me full resolution.

25:27.666 --> 25:29.083
[Jaq] Broken vase.

25:29.666 --> 25:31.250
I mean, defensive, maybe.

25:31.958 --> 25:33.250
Think Nicole
took a swing at them?

25:33.416 --> 25:34.416
[officer] We got it
right here.

25:34.583 --> 25:36.000
I'm gonna...
rotate it right now.

25:36.166 --> 25:37.083
Make sure
you double check that

25:37.250 --> 25:38.041
against the dispatch logs.

25:38.208 --> 25:40.208
[Jaq] Chris? You think
Nicole took a swing at them?

25:40.375 --> 25:42.416
Yeah. Yeah, maybe.

25:43.333 --> 25:44.708
[Jaq] Hey, can you
clear this out, please?

25:44.875 --> 25:45.958
[officer] You got it,
Detective.

25:48.000 --> 25:49.250
[Chris] Jaq,
get in the kitchen.

25:53.250 --> 25:54.583
[Jaq] I don't think
you wanna see this, Chris.

25:54.750 --> 25:56.125
Jaq, show me
what we got there.

25:58.208 --> 26:00.958
[Maddox] You may enter
the kitchen, Detective Diallo.

26:15.625 --> 26:16.875
[Chris] Whose footprints
are those?

26:17.750 --> 26:19.333
[Maddox] They belong
to your daughter.

26:19.833 --> 26:21.625
[Chris sighs] Jesus.

26:21.791 --> 26:23.375
[Jaq] We got a struggle here.

26:28.041 --> 26:29.583
[Chris] What's that?
Up by the countertop?

26:31.458 --> 26:33.958
Right there.
Far corner. Get close.

26:34.125 --> 26:35.791
[Maddox] Generating
scene reconstruction

26:35.958 --> 26:37.541
from trajectory data.

26:37.708 --> 26:38.958
[Chris] See that?

26:39.125 --> 26:40.791
I bet Nic threw that plate.

26:40.958 --> 26:42.208
Puts the suspect
in the kitchen.

26:42.375 --> 26:44.708
[Jaq] I mean,
Nic's backing up.

26:45.833 --> 26:47.125
Maybe throwing plates
as she goes.

26:47.291 --> 26:49.416
He lunges. So,
he's already got the knife.

26:50.916 --> 26:52.416
[Jaq] The knife
was an easy grab.

26:53.750 --> 26:55.041
All right,
let me see the prints.

27:10.333 --> 27:11.583
Nic was kinda scared
of that knife.

27:11.750 --> 27:13.083
I always did the prep.

27:15.083 --> 27:16.083
What about fibers?

27:22.583 --> 27:24.291
Fibers all match stuff
in the closet, Jaq.

27:24.708 --> 27:27.083
My hair, my skin,
my DNA's all over the place.

27:30.541 --> 27:32.208
You're thinking it. Spill it.

27:32.708 --> 27:35.416
It's a classic crime
of passion, Chris. I mean...

27:35.583 --> 27:37.083
the explosion of violence...

27:37.250 --> 27:38.791
grabbing the nearest weapon...

27:39.541 --> 27:40.541
the blood.

27:42.000 --> 27:43.500
And it all points
right at you.

27:47.333 --> 27:48.750
-[Maddox] Mr. Raven?
-No, she's right.

27:48.916 --> 27:50.708
It's a textbook
crime of passion.

27:52.750 --> 27:54.041
If that's what it is,
we need to work it like one.

27:54.208 --> 27:55.708
Can I see Nic's phone records?

27:58.333 --> 27:59.666
This is an interactive
virtual copy

27:59.833 --> 28:01.250
of Nicole's cell phone.

28:01.416 --> 28:02.958
The password
has been bypassed.

28:07.000 --> 28:08.291
All right, I need to see...

28:08.458 --> 28:10.000
Can I see the call history?

28:10.166 --> 28:11.791
Yeah... any number
she hasn't saved.

28:11.958 --> 28:13.583
[Maddox] 33% of calls
and messages

28:13.750 --> 28:15.333
were to and from
your cell phone...

28:15.500 --> 28:16.916
26% were Britt's...

28:17.083 --> 28:18.500
10 to her parents...

28:18.666 --> 28:20.125
the remainder are
to friends and colleagues...

28:20.291 --> 28:21.500
-at Viking Shipping.
-[Chris] Wait.

28:21.666 --> 28:23.916
That night we fought,
she was texting someone.

28:24.083 --> 28:25.666
Can I see
Britt's videos again?

28:29.791 --> 28:31.375
I mean, you know I was banking
on the lieutenant's spot...

28:31.541 --> 28:33.291
-to pay for it.
-Britt needs her own space.

28:33.458 --> 28:34.750
You've been promising it
for months.

28:35.375 --> 28:37.041
It's a basement.
All it needs is drywall.

28:37.208 --> 28:38.083
[Chris] You need
to back off of me!

28:38.250 --> 28:39.166
[Nicole] Back off?

28:39.416 --> 28:40.875
[Chris] Write a damn blog
about it.

28:42.291 --> 28:43.750
-Who are you talking to?
-[Chris] See, right there?

28:43.916 --> 28:45.625
-Nobody.
-[Chris] I knew she was.

28:45.791 --> 28:46.708
It's work.

28:46.875 --> 28:48.583
[Chris] Find out who
she was texting. Right there.

28:48.750 --> 28:50.000
[Maddox] I have
scanned her phone.

28:50.166 --> 28:52.416
There is no record of her
texting anyone at that time.

28:52.583 --> 28:53.583
What about her work phone?

28:54.250 --> 28:56.041
I have no record
of a second phone.

28:56.208 --> 28:57.583
Hey, you find
another cell in here?

28:57.750 --> 28:58.833
[officer] Nope.
No other phone.

28:59.000 --> 29:00.958
Of course they didn't.
They weren't looking for one.

29:01.125 --> 29:02.416
I mean, can you call it?

29:02.583 --> 29:04.625
-I don't know the number.
-Have you ever called it?

29:06.708 --> 29:07.708
What? You're in my phone?

29:07.875 --> 29:09.125
It's registered
to the municipal cloud

29:09.291 --> 29:10.875
and available
to the court so, yes.

29:11.666 --> 29:13.000
Well, Viking gave it to her...

29:13.166 --> 29:15.625
I think six months ago,
I might have called it then.

29:15.791 --> 29:17.000
Yeah, that's it.

29:17.166 --> 29:18.375
I was held up in juvie court.
She wanted me to come home...

29:18.541 --> 29:19.875
and look at furniture
for the basement.

29:20.041 --> 29:20.791
[line ringing]

29:22.375 --> 29:24.666
I mean, maybe it's on silent.

29:26.041 --> 29:28.125
[Reed] Detective,
we got a phone out here.

29:30.750 --> 29:32.458
-[indistinct chatter]
-[line continues ringing]

29:32.625 --> 29:33.750
[siren blaring]

29:40.583 --> 29:42.041
Detective Diallo,
could you please ensure...

29:42.208 --> 29:44.375
the Bluetooth on your phone
is switched on?

29:44.541 --> 29:46.166
Hold the two handsets
together.

29:49.458 --> 29:50.833
This is not a work phone.

29:51.000 --> 29:53.000
This is a black market
SIM unit.

29:53.166 --> 29:55.208
You would call it a burner.

29:55.375 --> 29:56.958
It's not registered
to the municipal cloud...

29:57.125 --> 29:58.291
and could not
have been provided

29:58.458 --> 29:59.541
by your wife's company.

29:59.708 --> 30:01.875
There is only one number
in the call history.

30:02.041 --> 30:03.750
The other number
called from this handset...

30:03.916 --> 30:05.916
is also a black market SIM...

30:06.083 --> 30:07.541
not registered to the cloud.

30:07.708 --> 30:09.708
[Jaq] Two burners.
Chris, I mean...

30:09.875 --> 30:10.791
-Yeah, it's all right.
-[Jaq] I mean,

30:10.958 --> 30:11.916
if it was a guy
she was calling...

30:12.083 --> 30:13.041
[Chris] Yeah, I know.

30:13.208 --> 30:14.250
Any suspect's
a good one right now.

30:15.083 --> 30:15.916
Can you locate
the other phone?

30:16.083 --> 30:17.000
It's not active on any relay.

30:17.166 --> 30:18.500
Well, can you wake it up?

30:23.958 --> 30:25.708
You're speaking
with the Mercy Capital Court.

30:25.875 --> 30:27.708
-Please state your...
-[line disconnects]

30:28.833 --> 30:30.125
The phone is somewhere
in the vicinity

30:30.291 --> 30:31.500
of the Hollywood Red Zone.

30:31.666 --> 30:33.291
[Jaq] Shit. With traffic
that'll take me 30 minutes.

30:33.458 --> 30:34.666
[Chris] Okay, Jaq,
you won't make it

30:34.833 --> 30:35.708
through traffic in time.

30:35.875 --> 30:38.125
You need to get in the air
for me, fast.

30:38.666 --> 30:40.666
Detective Diallo,
please proceed.

30:41.416 --> 30:42.416
Okay.

30:42.583 --> 30:44.708
Hey, get my vest
out of my unit.

30:44.875 --> 30:46.250
You already
suspected your wife

30:46.416 --> 30:48.208
may have been
keeping things from you?

30:48.375 --> 30:49.958
[Chris] Yeah, maybe.

30:50.125 --> 30:51.375
So, what, right?

30:51.541 --> 30:52.541
Come on, everybody lies.

30:54.875 --> 30:55.875
Apart from you.

30:59.833 --> 31:02.041
This is Detective Diallo,
RHD...

31:02.208 --> 31:04.500
I'm entering your airspace
over the Hollywood Red Zone...

31:04.666 --> 31:05.791
tracking the suspect.

31:05.958 --> 31:07.041
All units, be on standby

31:07.208 --> 31:09.041
to give me backup
if I call for it.

31:13.750 --> 31:14.791
I should inform you now

31:14.958 --> 31:16.083
that your probability
of guilt...

31:16.250 --> 31:18.791
has reduced to 96.7%.

31:19.166 --> 31:20.458
[sarcastically] Wow,
that's peachy.

31:23.833 --> 31:25.208
[indistinct police
radio chatter]

31:25.375 --> 31:27.916
[officer] Control to air four,
we have tally on Red Zone LZ.

31:28.083 --> 31:31.208
That zone is hot and active.
Multiple 415s.

31:31.375 --> 31:32.541
[officer 2] Detective Diallo,

31:32.708 --> 31:34.000
be advised you're entering
a Red Zone.

31:34.166 --> 31:35.333
Maintain altitude.

31:35.500 --> 31:37.750
Hostiles may try
to hijack the copter.

31:37.916 --> 31:39.000
[Jaq] I'm a minute out.

31:39.916 --> 31:42.166
You're putting me right
on the edge of a Red Zone.

31:42.333 --> 31:43.958
[all clamoring]

31:45.833 --> 31:47.291
-[officer 3] Get up.
-[Chris] Shit.

31:48.166 --> 31:50.125
It's gonna be impossible
to find him through that mess.

31:52.166 --> 31:53.166
Reed, where are you?

31:53.833 --> 31:54.833
We're almost caught up to you.

31:55.000 --> 31:57.333
Chris, you gotta give me
an exact location.

31:57.500 --> 31:58.458
Come on. Where is he, Maddox?

31:58.625 --> 32:00.333
[Maddox] I'm gonna attempt
to reset the tracker.

32:02.958 --> 32:04.500
Cell phone
signal lock acquired.

32:04.666 --> 32:07.083
Phone is inside
the Hudson Hotel.

32:07.250 --> 32:08.958
It appears he's attempting
to exit the building...

32:09.125 --> 32:10.625
via the rear service doors.

32:10.791 --> 32:12.166
Detective Diallo, do you copy?

32:12.333 --> 32:13.083
Got it.

32:16.375 --> 32:17.375
[quadcopter whirring]

32:20.791 --> 32:23.416
Stop, LAPD.
Stay where you are!

32:25.041 --> 32:26.041
[officer 4] We got him, Jaq.

32:27.750 --> 32:28.750
[Howard] Stop right there!

32:29.916 --> 32:31.166
[Maddox] Patrick Burke, 36.

32:31.333 --> 32:33.125
Sous-chef at the Hudson Hotel.

32:33.291 --> 32:34.375
He's late on his rent

32:34.541 --> 32:35.666
and has been
investigated twice...

32:35.833 --> 32:37.750
for Social Security fraud.

32:37.916 --> 32:38.916
How's my guilt looking now?

32:39.083 --> 32:41.166
Holding at 96.7%.

32:41.333 --> 32:43.250
Are you kidding me?
Come on, guilty people run.

32:43.416 --> 32:44.708
As do frightened people.

32:44.875 --> 32:46.583
I'm guessing this asshole's
a little bit of both.

32:46.750 --> 32:47.750
[Reed] Hey! Hey!

32:49.500 --> 32:50.583
[woman screams]

32:51.500 --> 32:53.625
[Reed] Where'd he go?
Where'd he go?

32:53.791 --> 32:54.791
Well, where was he?

32:56.291 --> 32:57.375
Yo, what's going on,
everybody?

32:57.541 --> 32:59.208
You're in the kitchen
with Chef Burke.

32:59.791 --> 33:01.500
[Chris] Looks like
he's comfortable with a knife.

33:01.666 --> 33:02.875
Jaq, that's him!

33:03.041 --> 33:04.833
Chef, Chef, I need you guys
to cover for me, okay?

33:05.000 --> 33:07.125
They're chasing me.
I don't know why.

33:07.291 --> 33:08.458
-[officer] Move, now!
-Where's that door go?

33:08.625 --> 33:09.625
-[Reed] Where'd he go?
-Undetermined.

33:09.791 --> 33:10.958
There are no cameras coverage
in that area.

33:11.125 --> 33:12.125
[Reed] Damn it!

33:12.291 --> 33:13.708
Hell, Detective Diallo,
I'm really sorry...

33:13.875 --> 33:15.125
-we lost him.
-Shit!

33:15.291 --> 33:16.375
Releasing the tracking drone.

33:16.541 --> 33:17.666
[drone whirring]

33:18.250 --> 33:19.291
Wait, are you still
tracking his cell?

33:19.458 --> 33:20.458
Signal is intermittent,

33:20.625 --> 33:21.708
but appears
to be moving upwards.

33:21.875 --> 33:23.416
Detective Diallo, do you copy?

33:23.583 --> 33:24.583
[Jaq] Copy.

33:25.291 --> 33:26.833
[Reed] Jaq,
we're headin' your way now.

33:33.666 --> 33:34.666
[quadcopter stops whirring]

33:36.083 --> 33:37.666
[Jaq] I don't see him.

33:37.833 --> 33:39.000
Chris, you guys see him?

33:39.166 --> 33:40.583
[Chris] Jaq,
he's at your 6 o'clock.

33:43.875 --> 33:46.458
[Jaq] LAPD. Stop! Stop!

33:51.958 --> 33:52.916
-[Reed] Go to the other side!
-[Howard] Go.

33:53.083 --> 33:54.791
-Go around, go around.
-[Burke] No, no, no.

33:54.958 --> 33:56.083
-[Reed] Go, go, go.
-[Jaq] Hey!

33:56.250 --> 33:57.458
-[Howard] Hey!
-[Jaq] Hey, stop!

33:57.625 --> 33:58.625
-[Reed] Burke!
-[Jaq] Hey!

33:58.791 --> 34:00.708
-[Reed] He's slowin' down!
-[Jaq] Hey!

34:02.208 --> 34:03.166
[Chris] Jaq!

34:03.333 --> 34:04.666
[Burke screams, grunts]

34:07.500 --> 34:08.500
[Jaq grunts]

34:11.166 --> 34:12.750
-Come on, Jaq.
-[Burke grunting]

34:20.583 --> 34:21.625
Jaq, Jaq,
I don't have time for this.

34:21.791 --> 34:22.833
I need to talk to him
right now.

34:23.000 --> 34:23.708
[Jaq] Stay right there!
Don't move!

34:23.875 --> 34:24.625
-Don't move!
-Mr. Burke,

34:24.791 --> 34:25.708
you're speaking with...
the Mercy Court chamber.

34:25.875 --> 34:26.666
You must be truthful
at all times.

34:26.833 --> 34:28.250
[Burke] Listen, I didn't
do anything, all right?

34:28.416 --> 34:29.666
You have to believe me.
I didn't do anything.

34:29.833 --> 34:30.833
[Jaq] If you didn't
do anything,

34:31.000 --> 34:31.875
why the hell are you running?

34:32.041 --> 34:32.833
[Burke] What do you mean,
"why the hell"?

34:33.000 --> 34:33.916
Listen to me...

34:34.083 --> 34:36.291
I got a call from some lady
talking about Mercy.

34:36.458 --> 34:37.541
So yeah,
I freak out, all right?

34:38.083 --> 34:40.625
Then I check my news feed,
and I see that Nicole's dead?

34:40.791 --> 34:42.458
I'm not sticking around
for that shit to land.

34:42.625 --> 34:43.416
That's why I ran.

34:43.583 --> 34:44.583
-[Jaq] All right, relax.
-What a deadbeat.

34:45.958 --> 34:46.708
-What?
-[Chris] I said,

34:46.833 --> 34:47.583
"What the hell is Nic doing...

34:47.750 --> 34:48.750
"with a deadbeat like you?"

34:48.916 --> 34:49.916
Mr. Raven.

34:50.083 --> 34:51.416
-What was she doing with me?
-[Jaq] You need to relax.

34:51.583 --> 34:53.083
What was she doing with me?
She was getting everything...

34:53.250 --> 34:54.041
that you couldn't give her.

34:54.208 --> 34:54.916
-That's what!
-[Jaq] Shut...

34:55.083 --> 34:56.958
-All right.
-Mr. Burke, remain calm...

34:57.125 --> 34:58.875
and I expect
no further insults...

34:59.041 --> 35:01.541
directed at Mr. Burke
from you.

35:01.708 --> 35:03.166
Why don't you just tell me
about you and Nic.

35:03.333 --> 35:04.500
[Burke] Okay.

35:04.666 --> 35:07.375
We met at the farmers market
that she goes to and...

35:07.541 --> 35:08.375
[sighs]

35:08.541 --> 35:09.625
I don't know. She's...

35:09.791 --> 35:11.625
She's beautiful, all right,
so you know how it is.

35:11.791 --> 35:13.791
I hit her
with a few compliments.

35:13.958 --> 35:16.291
Then I see her
a couple of weeks later...

35:16.458 --> 35:18.458
and then I ask her
to meet me for coffee.

35:18.625 --> 35:19.875
We met up just like that...

35:20.041 --> 35:22.041
a few more times
a few weeks apart...

35:22.208 --> 35:23.333
that's all.

35:23.500 --> 35:25.000
-Why'd she have a burner?
-Listen, she said that...

35:25.166 --> 35:26.500
we had to be
able to talk privately.

35:26.666 --> 35:27.666
Okay?

35:27.833 --> 35:28.833
So, I told her
that I knew a guy

35:29.000 --> 35:30.083
that could get her a phone...

35:30.250 --> 35:31.791
off the grid.
None of that cloud shit.

35:31.958 --> 35:34.125
Records show that you own
a cloud registered phone...

35:34.291 --> 35:35.625
in addition to
your black-market handset.

35:35.791 --> 35:38.125
Yeah, I've got two phones.
So what?

35:39.208 --> 35:40.166
[Chris] Wait,
what are you doing?

35:40.333 --> 35:41.416
[Maddox] Accessing his cloud
registered device...

35:41.583 --> 35:43.375
and correlating his movements
with Nicole's...

35:43.541 --> 35:44.916
based on tracking data.

35:45.083 --> 35:45.958
Mr. Burke, could you outline

35:46.125 --> 35:47.958
the contact with Nicole Raven,
please?

35:49.375 --> 35:50.750
We met here once a week.

35:51.166 --> 35:53.041
She loved it
when I cooked just for her.

35:53.833 --> 35:55.208
[Nicole chuckles] Oh, hey.

35:56.208 --> 35:57.208
[Burke chuckles]

35:59.250 --> 36:00.291
[Nicole] I missed you.

36:02.083 --> 36:03.208
That's enough.
I get it, I get it.

36:03.375 --> 36:04.208
Where were you
going this morning?

36:04.375 --> 36:05.250
[Burke] I was here...

36:05.416 --> 36:07.125
running breakfast service.
All right?

36:07.291 --> 36:09.333
And there's a whole team here
to back me up on that.

36:16.625 --> 36:17.666
[indistinct chatter]

36:28.500 --> 36:29.625
-It's not him.
-[Jaq] Stop moving.

36:29.791 --> 36:30.625
[Burke] You're not putting me
in that chair.

36:30.791 --> 36:31.583
[Jaq] I said,
I said stop moving!

36:31.750 --> 36:32.916
[Howard and Reed]
Move it! Move it!

36:33.083 --> 36:34.208
Mr. Raven,
please speak clearly.

36:34.375 --> 36:36.291
I said, it's not him.

36:36.458 --> 36:37.958
Yeah, that's what I've been
trying to tell you.

36:38.125 --> 36:39.125
[Maddox] Thank you, Mr. Burke.

36:39.291 --> 36:41.083
The facts do not lie
and neither have you.

36:41.250 --> 36:42.291
This court is very satisfied

36:42.458 --> 36:44.583
that your version of events
is accurate.

36:45.500 --> 36:47.166
[Burke] You really blew it,
you know that, right?

36:47.333 --> 36:48.833
She just needed
somebody to talk to.

36:49.333 --> 36:50.208
Somebody to listen to her,

36:50.375 --> 36:51.791
-about your daughter...
-[Jaq] Enough, enough.

36:51.958 --> 36:53.125
...about all that
crap at work.

36:53.291 --> 36:54.583
All you had to do
was focus a little bit more

36:54.750 --> 36:56.250
on your kid and your wife...

36:56.416 --> 36:57.833
-but instead you killed her.
-[Jaq] Okay, enough, enough.

36:58.000 --> 36:58.875
I guess she was right
about your...

36:59.041 --> 37:00.125
-anger problem.
-[Jaq] Cuff him. Arrest him.

37:00.291 --> 37:01.125
-Now. Arrest him.
-Arrest me for what?

37:01.291 --> 37:02.583
-He just said I was...
-[Jaq] Resisting arrest.

37:02.750 --> 37:04.666
-He just said it wasn't me.
-Pissing me off!

37:05.333 --> 37:07.083
And making my officers
run around like assholes...

37:07.250 --> 37:09.000
chasing you around
the whole building!

37:16.333 --> 37:17.958
[Maddox] Your probability
of guilt...

37:18.125 --> 37:20.875
has now risen to 98%.

37:21.666 --> 37:22.666
How'd that happen?

37:22.833 --> 37:25.083
Instead of providing the court
with another suspect...

37:25.250 --> 37:27.041
you have provided it
with a strong motive...

37:27.208 --> 37:29.333
of why you may have
committed the crime.

37:31.541 --> 37:33.208
[sarcastically] Well,
at least it's not 100%.

37:33.375 --> 37:34.958
It is not
statistically possible...

37:35.125 --> 37:37.708
to exceed 98% in this court.

37:39.875 --> 37:41.916
Did you really believe that
you would find evidence...

37:42.083 --> 37:43.500
to exonerate yourself?

37:43.666 --> 37:45.208
Or did you just simply
want to meet the man...

37:45.375 --> 37:46.666
that your wife was seeing?

37:50.833 --> 37:52.000
You think I killed Nic
'cause I found out

37:52.166 --> 37:53.166
she was seeing someone?

37:53.333 --> 37:54.958
What, you think
this is all an act?

37:55.125 --> 37:57.000
I think there's more
that you're not revealing.

37:57.875 --> 37:59.375
You were very quick
to look for an affair.

37:59.541 --> 38:00.833
'Cause I suspected
something...

38:01.833 --> 38:02.875
Maybe. I mean,
I didn't know for sure,

38:03.041 --> 38:04.208
but I'm not surprised.

38:05.333 --> 38:06.541
Not now. Just, it's...

38:06.708 --> 38:08.416
I guess I just kept
lettin' her down.

38:11.833 --> 38:12.833
Even today.

38:13.666 --> 38:14.666
Today?

38:19.250 --> 38:21.000
She found my booze stash.

38:22.291 --> 38:23.958
I keep a... flask in my car.

38:24.125 --> 38:26.041
I mean, flask sounds fancy.

38:26.208 --> 38:27.250
It's an old soda bottle.

38:27.416 --> 38:30.000
It's brown, so you can't
tell it's whiskey.

38:31.541 --> 38:32.541
Smart, huh?

38:32.708 --> 38:35.166
How long have you been
drinking again?

38:36.291 --> 38:37.666
Well... about a year.

38:40.250 --> 38:41.666
[slow rock music playing
over speakers]

38:49.208 --> 38:50.541
[Nicole] What's going on
in here?

38:50.708 --> 38:51.583
This has to stop.

38:51.750 --> 38:52.708
[Chris] Why are you
filming me?

38:52.875 --> 38:53.875
[Nicole] Don't come
any closer.

38:54.041 --> 38:55.583
I'm not giving you the phone.

38:55.750 --> 38:57.041
I'm not giving you the phone.
I said...

38:57.208 --> 38:59.541
-"Don't come any closer."
-Why were you filming me?

38:59.708 --> 39:01.541
-I am filming you because...
-Why were you filming me?

39:01.708 --> 39:03.333
I am filming you
because I need you

39:03.500 --> 39:05.250
to watch it when you're sober.
All right?

39:05.416 --> 39:08.166
They were all so damn proud
of me after I got sober.

39:08.333 --> 39:09.583
Nic, Britt, Rob.

39:09.750 --> 39:12.166
Called AA. I'm going to
my first meeting on Tuesday.

39:18.291 --> 39:19.333
I miss you.

39:20.083 --> 39:21.125
I miss you both.

39:22.333 --> 39:23.750
One year.

39:23.916 --> 39:25.083
[Nicole] One year.

39:25.666 --> 39:27.125
-And one day.
-One year and one day.

39:27.291 --> 39:28.375
I got it yesterday.

39:28.958 --> 39:29.958
That went by fast.

39:30.125 --> 39:31.708
[Nicole] That went by fast.
You did so well.

39:32.416 --> 39:34.375
-Thank you.
-My pleasure.

39:34.541 --> 39:35.791
I don't think
I can do it four times...

39:35.958 --> 39:37.541
so I might have to start
drinkin' again.

39:37.708 --> 39:39.208
-[all laughing]
-I couldn't shake it.

39:41.250 --> 39:42.750
It kept getting on top of me.

39:42.916 --> 39:45.250
[Maddox] Mr. Raven,
what are you talking about?

39:45.416 --> 39:46.416
Ray.

39:46.958 --> 39:48.791
Your former partner's death?

39:52.250 --> 39:53.250
No.

39:54.375 --> 39:55.833
What I should
have done about it.

39:57.083 --> 39:59.083
Whiskey-45,
we're 11-96 on that possible

39:59.250 --> 40:00.416
hit-and-run SUV.

40:01.541 --> 40:03.916
California plates
three David, Henry, Ida, 832.

40:04.083 --> 40:05.583
PCH south of Topanga.

40:06.208 --> 40:07.083
Well, looks like

40:07.250 --> 40:08.500
-they dumped it and booked.
-Yeah.

40:08.666 --> 40:09.666
[dispatcher] Vehicle confirms

40:09.833 --> 40:11.166
-for wants and warrants.
-10-4.

40:11.333 --> 40:12.333
-All right, let's check it.
-[phone ringing]

40:13.500 --> 40:15.375
Yeah.
Can't talk, Nic.

40:15.541 --> 40:16.833
No, no, no.

40:17.000 --> 40:18.333
Talk to your woman.
I got this.

40:18.500 --> 40:19.500
[Chris sighs]

40:20.666 --> 40:22.333
Yeah, yeah. No, he's good.

40:23.791 --> 40:24.958
No, I didn't, babe.

40:27.000 --> 40:29.208
No. Nic, Nic, just...

40:29.375 --> 40:30.333
Honey, you gotta dial it back.

40:30.500 --> 40:31.291
What do you want me to do?

40:31.458 --> 40:32.250
You want me to walk
into my chief's office...

40:32.416 --> 40:33.791
tell him my wife's
got a petition for him?

40:33.958 --> 40:36.458
She wants us to reopen
a slam dunk investigation?

40:37.125 --> 40:38.083
"She's got
a lot of signatures.

40:38.250 --> 40:39.333
"She'll ask really nicely?"

40:39.833 --> 40:41.000
[Chris chuckles]

40:41.166 --> 40:42.625
No, I'm not. It's just...

40:44.500 --> 40:47.500
Baby, it makes it worse
that your dad's defending...

40:47.666 --> 40:48.541
-[Ray] Gun! Gun!
-[gunshots]

40:48.708 --> 40:49.750
-There's two of 'em!
-[Chris] Ray.

40:49.916 --> 40:51.541
-There's two. Chris! Chris!
-[Chris] Ray.

40:51.625 --> 40:52.791
-Ray!
-[groans]

40:52.958 --> 40:54.291
You sure you're good, brother?

40:54.458 --> 40:55.875
I make one turn,
we're at UCLA ER in five.

40:56.041 --> 40:57.041
No, it's not broke!

40:57.208 --> 40:58.625
Stay on 'em
and get that piece of shit.

40:58.791 --> 41:00.458
[Chris] Officer Vale
has been shot. I'm gonna pit.

41:00.625 --> 41:01.750
I need a medivac now!

41:01.916 --> 41:03.041
[dispatcher 2] Ambulance
is en route. Over.

41:04.166 --> 41:05.916
[Chris] Hey.
Hey, hold on, Ray.

41:06.083 --> 41:07.500
Hey, stay with me, Ray.

41:07.666 --> 41:08.625
Ray!

41:08.791 --> 41:10.208
[siren blaring]

41:11.875 --> 41:12.875
[tires screeching]

41:14.666 --> 41:15.625
[body thuds]

41:17.750 --> 41:18.958
[Chris grunts]

41:19.666 --> 41:21.791
Ray! Ray, talk to me, Ray!

41:23.125 --> 41:25.375
Officer down! Officer down!

41:25.958 --> 41:28.000
[officer] This is Henry
one-three. Copy that.

41:28.583 --> 41:29.916
[Chris] Hey,
get on the ground!

41:30.083 --> 41:31.041
We got a runner.

41:37.708 --> 41:39.041
Police! Stop!

41:39.208 --> 41:41.166
I shoulda done it myself
on that beach.

41:41.333 --> 41:42.791
-Stop!
-[birds cawing]

41:44.791 --> 41:46.625
Get over here! Freeze!

41:48.875 --> 41:50.416
Turn around.
Put your hands on your head.

41:50.583 --> 41:51.750
I should have killed him.

41:52.750 --> 41:53.916
[handcuffs clinking]

41:54.083 --> 41:56.875
There isn't a day that goes by
that I don't wish I had.

41:58.791 --> 42:00.583
[foreperson] Verdict 4-B,
we the jury...

42:00.750 --> 42:02.375
find the defendant,
Alex Varga...

42:02.541 --> 42:03.625
not guilty of the murder

42:03.791 --> 42:04.916
-of Ray Vale.
-[people cheering]

42:05.083 --> 42:07.000
[Chris] I thought I was doing
the right thing.

42:07.166 --> 42:08.458
Catch the bad guy...

42:08.625 --> 42:10.458
let the courts punish him...

42:10.625 --> 42:11.625
but they didn't.

42:14.416 --> 42:16.708
I guess getting a buzz on
just kinda... dulled it.

42:16.875 --> 42:18.333
Mr. Raven,
you're losing your focus.

42:18.500 --> 42:20.041
Could you just tell me
what you really remember?

42:29.208 --> 42:30.958
[Chris] I pulled up
to work this morning...

42:31.125 --> 42:32.375
reached for the bottle.

42:32.541 --> 42:33.541
It wasn't there.

42:33.708 --> 42:35.125
I knew straightaway
she found it.

42:35.291 --> 42:36.250
So, I drove home.

42:36.416 --> 42:37.583
And you argued with her?

42:37.750 --> 42:39.000
Of course I argued with her.

42:40.750 --> 42:42.583
She went crazy at me
for falling off the wagon.

42:42.750 --> 42:44.166
I went crazy
right back at her...

42:44.333 --> 42:46.791
'cause she'd already thrown
my bottle in the recycling.

42:51.166 --> 42:53.458
[Nicole] Do not come in here!
Get out of my house!

42:53.625 --> 42:55.541
Get out of my house!
Don't you dare.

42:55.708 --> 42:56.958
[Chris] You locked me
out of my own house?

42:57.125 --> 42:58.125
[Nicole] It is not your house!

42:58.291 --> 42:59.416
[Chris] Tell me
where you put it.

42:59.583 --> 43:00.708
Where is my flask?

43:00.875 --> 43:02.083
-[object shattering]
-[Nicole gasps]

43:04.708 --> 43:06.375
So, I broke her favorite vase.

43:08.791 --> 43:10.125
I threw it on the floor...

43:10.291 --> 43:11.791
'cause I knew how much
it meant to her.

43:13.250 --> 43:14.875
Some of the glass shot up.
It cut her.

43:15.041 --> 43:16.250
I tried to help, but I figured

43:16.416 --> 43:17.666
that's how I got
her blood on me.

43:17.833 --> 43:19.750
And why did you not
admit this earlier?

43:19.916 --> 43:21.833
Oh, come on. Not a good look.

43:22.000 --> 43:23.166
Everything I just told you

43:23.333 --> 43:25.291
is only making this
worse for me.

43:28.416 --> 43:29.791
And after that...

43:29.958 --> 43:32.500
I truly don't remember...
anything.

43:32.666 --> 43:34.666
I'm in the house
arguing with her.

43:35.375 --> 43:36.750
Next thing you know...

43:37.416 --> 43:39.833
I'm watching a frickin'
commercial for Mercy Court.

43:40.000 --> 43:41.000
[Britt] Mom?

43:42.291 --> 43:44.708
[Chris] I guess if she got mad
enough to tell me about Burke.

43:46.541 --> 43:47.458
I'm just saying...

43:47.625 --> 43:49.500
[Britt screaming]

43:49.666 --> 43:51.125
...maybe you got a point
about motive.

43:51.291 --> 43:52.166
[Maddox] Mr. Raven...

43:52.333 --> 43:55.291
If I was already angry,
maybe I grabbed the knife...

43:55.458 --> 43:56.750
If you admit guilt...

43:56.916 --> 43:59.208
this court obligates me
to lock a verdict...

43:59.375 --> 44:02.083
and then you will simply just
watch the clock count down.

44:02.250 --> 44:04.583
98%. Maddox, come on.

44:04.750 --> 44:06.000
If your memory of the events

44:06.166 --> 44:07.375
that transpired
in the house...

44:07.541 --> 44:09.250
with Nicole
is truly incomplete...

44:10.208 --> 44:11.250
then an honest confession
of guilt

44:11.416 --> 44:12.375
is beyond your capacity.

44:13.208 --> 44:14.416
Your guilt percentage,
however...

44:14.583 --> 44:17.833
remains more than high enough
to result in your execution...

44:18.000 --> 44:20.458
but you still have
my full capabilities

44:20.625 --> 44:21.958
at your disposal.

44:22.291 --> 44:23.916
So, if you are to die today...

44:24.916 --> 44:26.958
do you not want to at least
attempt to uncover...

44:27.125 --> 44:29.458
the truth with certainty
before you do?

44:31.333 --> 44:33.291
Even if the truth is dark.

44:35.208 --> 44:36.375
Well, that's just it.

44:39.875 --> 44:41.541
Maybe I don't wanna
know for sure.

44:42.541 --> 44:44.041
I mean, the way
I see it right now...

44:44.791 --> 44:46.458
the only thing left
that makes me think

44:46.625 --> 44:48.625
maybe I didn't kill Nic
is wondering...

44:48.791 --> 44:51.291
how the hell I could
commit a crime of passion

44:51.458 --> 44:53.458
when there was
no passion left.

45:07.750 --> 45:09.083
Shit.

45:09.250 --> 45:13.041
I... I mean, do you think
that could be it?

45:13.208 --> 45:14.416
I do not know what "it" is.

45:14.583 --> 45:16.375
Maddox, I'm just
thinkin' out loud.

45:16.541 --> 45:18.166
Thinking is inherently silent
due to the brain's...

45:18.333 --> 45:20.416
It's an expression,
Your Honor.

45:22.166 --> 45:23.125
So, I can keep going?

45:23.291 --> 45:25.041
I can keep looking
for evidence, you're saying?

45:25.208 --> 45:26.083
Providing you do not

45:26.250 --> 45:27.291
inadvertently confess
to murder...

45:27.458 --> 45:29.416
yes, you may use
the remaining time.

45:31.291 --> 45:32.291
[Chris] Who?

45:32.791 --> 45:33.791
Why?

45:35.000 --> 45:36.833
-How?
-Mr. Raven?

45:37.000 --> 45:38.333
Still thinkin' out loud, here.

45:40.208 --> 45:42.375
Can you show me everyone
Nic had regular contact with?

45:42.541 --> 45:44.458
The protocols of this court
require me to point out...

45:44.625 --> 45:45.833
that embarking on a full-blown

45:46.000 --> 45:47.291
murder investigation
with just...

45:47.958 --> 45:49.541
40 minutes available to you...

45:49.708 --> 45:50.458
-[Chris] Good. Wow.
-...carries with it

45:50.625 --> 45:52.000
an extremely
low probability of success.

45:52.166 --> 45:53.250
You know... What?
You want me to sit here...

45:53.416 --> 45:55.458
and wait to die? You just
stopped me from confessing!

45:55.625 --> 45:56.541
This court is simply ensuring

45:56.708 --> 45:58.041
-that you are fully aware...
-All right, you really

45:58.208 --> 45:59.083
-had me going there.
-...of the fact that you...

45:59.250 --> 46:00.416
I thought, for a second,

46:00.583 --> 46:03.000
this place might not be
a kill box after all.

46:05.541 --> 46:06.583
[Maddox] This is
every individual

46:06.750 --> 46:08.375
your wife
had regular contact with.

46:08.541 --> 46:10.541
[intriguing music playing]

46:11.500 --> 46:12.583
Thank you, Your Honor.

46:16.875 --> 46:17.875
With a planned murder,

46:18.041 --> 46:19.375
you usually know
the victim well.

46:21.416 --> 46:23.208
We can lose Burke already.

46:24.083 --> 46:25.083
Parents, too.

46:27.875 --> 46:29.666
Can you split
friends and work?

46:37.000 --> 46:38.291
25 people.

46:38.458 --> 46:39.541
Add 'em to the board.

46:43.583 --> 46:44.708
Come on, Nic, who was it?

46:46.958 --> 46:48.041
[Chris chuckles wearily]

46:48.208 --> 46:50.166
Well, I guess he was right.

46:50.333 --> 46:51.666
-[Maddox] Who?
-[Chris] Burke.

46:52.208 --> 46:53.416
If I'd been there for her,

46:53.583 --> 46:54.875
maybe she'd have told me
about some of the...

46:55.041 --> 46:56.500
Somebody to listen to her,
about your daughter...

46:56.666 --> 46:57.583
[Jaq] All right,
enough, enough.

46:57.750 --> 46:58.666
...about all that
crap at work.

46:58.833 --> 47:00.375
All you had to do was
focus a little bit more on...

47:00.541 --> 47:03.041
Burke! I need Burke. Now.

47:04.000 --> 47:07.500
Mr. Burke is being
processed at... 77th Street.

47:09.333 --> 47:10.333
[officer] Processing.

47:10.500 --> 47:11.541
[Chris] Yeah, who's
your booking officer?

47:11.708 --> 47:14.458
-[officer] Me. Who's asking?
-Chris Raven, RHD.

47:14.625 --> 47:15.916
You got a Patrick Burke there.
I need him.

47:16.083 --> 47:17.083
[officer]
He's getting printed.

47:17.875 --> 47:19.750
Hold on, you say Raven?

47:19.916 --> 47:20.708
Aren't you the guy

47:20.875 --> 47:22.041
-who stuck...
-[Chris] Yeah, yeah, that guy.

47:22.500 --> 47:24.291
[officer] Well, I don't think
I should be puttin' him...

47:24.458 --> 47:26.875
Officer, this is Judge Maddox
at the Mercy Court.

47:27.041 --> 47:29.291
Please give Mr. Burke
your cellular phone.

47:29.458 --> 47:31.625
Uh, I'll get Burke now, uh...

47:31.791 --> 47:32.833
Thank you.

47:33.000 --> 47:34.416
Okay. Wanna call my HMO after?

47:34.583 --> 47:36.125
[Maddox] Health Maintenance
Organizations are...

47:36.291 --> 47:37.291
notorious for their red tape

47:37.458 --> 47:39.333
and frustratingly
slow functioning.

47:41.750 --> 47:42.833
So, you were making a joke.

47:43.500 --> 47:45.833
Look at you,
thinkin' out loud.

47:47.083 --> 47:48.083
[officer] Hey, Burke!

47:48.708 --> 47:50.750
-Yeah?
-You got a phone call.

47:51.541 --> 47:52.541
Who?

47:56.083 --> 47:57.125
-Raven?
-[Chris] You talk to me...

47:57.291 --> 47:58.416
or you talk to the judge.

47:59.125 --> 48:00.583
You said Nic needed
someone to listen.

48:00.750 --> 48:01.875
What was on her mind?

48:02.041 --> 48:03.333
Any problems with friends?

48:03.500 --> 48:04.500
[Burke] Nah.

48:04.916 --> 48:05.875
You know, it was the usual.

48:06.041 --> 48:08.625
The one with the baby thinks
the world revolves around her.

48:08.791 --> 48:10.375
The other one
never splits the bill fair.

48:10.541 --> 48:11.541
What about work?

48:12.125 --> 48:13.125
Wow. [exhales]

48:13.666 --> 48:15.791
Bro, you really dialed out,
didn't you?

48:17.791 --> 48:20.083
All right, look, I told her
it was no big deal...

48:20.250 --> 48:21.750
but she got
crazy stressed over it.

48:21.916 --> 48:23.750
She didn't like the snooping.

48:23.916 --> 48:25.625
-What are you talking about?
-She didn't tell you?

48:25.791 --> 48:28.000
You know, the snoopin'.
Looking into her coworkers...

48:28.166 --> 48:30.333
because of that...
stuff went missing.

48:31.291 --> 48:32.958
I can't remember what
she said it was called...

48:33.125 --> 48:35.083
but it was some chemical
that they were shipping out.

48:35.250 --> 48:37.166
-All they ship is chemicals!
-Yeah, I know.

48:37.333 --> 48:39.458
I know, but I don't remember
what it was called, all right?

48:39.625 --> 48:41.250
But I do know that her boss...

48:41.416 --> 48:43.708
he was worried that
someone was swiping the stuff.

48:44.250 --> 48:46.041
I mean, it wasn't even much.
It was, like...

48:46.208 --> 48:48.958
what? A couple grand worth
every few months?

48:49.541 --> 48:51.541
After that, some customer got
into it with him over it...

48:51.708 --> 48:54.083
so that's when they asked
Nicole to check it out.

48:54.708 --> 48:57.958
And, like I said, she wasn't
comfortable doing that.

48:58.625 --> 49:00.541
That's all I know, all right?

49:01.958 --> 49:03.250
Look, you wouldn't
even have to ask me if you...

49:03.416 --> 49:04.958
Hey, Burke?
Go screw yourself.

49:06.000 --> 49:07.166
Okay, we can lose the friends.

49:15.208 --> 49:16.291
All right,
where are they all today?

49:16.458 --> 49:17.500
[Maddox] They're all at work.

49:17.666 --> 49:18.833
Nobody's been within a mile

49:19.000 --> 49:20.250
of your neighborhood
since Sunday.

49:20.416 --> 49:23.041
Yeah. We had a, we had
the barbecue. Where's Jaq?

49:27.500 --> 49:28.333
[Jaq] Detective.

49:28.500 --> 49:29.958
All right, we're gonna
come at this fresh.

49:30.541 --> 49:32.333
Looks like
a crime of passion, right?

49:32.500 --> 49:34.000
Textbook,
which only points at me.

49:34.166 --> 49:35.166
But what if it wasn't?

49:35.666 --> 49:37.958
The scene, though, Chris?
I mean, the blood.

49:38.125 --> 49:40.208
Look, we got 37 minutes,
Jaq, just play along.

49:40.375 --> 49:42.791
[Maddox] Detective Diallo,
please cooperate.

49:42.958 --> 49:43.708
-Okay, okay.
-[Chris] All right...

49:43.875 --> 49:45.000
I'm playin' a hunch.

49:45.166 --> 49:46.833
You need to get
to Viking Shipping Depot.

49:47.000 --> 49:48.000
[Jaq] Yup.

49:50.208 --> 49:52.000
You're playing a hunch?
What is a hunch?

49:52.166 --> 49:53.291
[Chris] Trusting my gut.

49:53.958 --> 49:54.958
And I'm beginning to think

49:55.125 --> 49:56.625
this court could do with
a little human intuition...

49:56.791 --> 49:58.083
This court deals
only in facts.

49:58.250 --> 50:00.000
The facts aren't where
the investigation ends.

50:00.166 --> 50:01.625
It's where it starts.

50:01.791 --> 50:02.916
Facts are black and white.

50:03.083 --> 50:05.458
The truth is always
in the gray in between.

50:05.625 --> 50:07.041
I guess this court
overlooked that.

50:08.208 --> 50:09.750
Or were you just
programmed wrong?

50:14.583 --> 50:16.583
Okay. I can't even remember
who half these people are.

50:18.375 --> 50:20.250
Did Britt film anything
at the barbecue?

50:23.458 --> 50:24.666
-[Britt] Hello.
-[Rob] How are ya?

50:24.833 --> 50:26.333
-[Britt] Good.
-That'll get you likes.

50:26.500 --> 50:27.791
-Oh, yeah. Yes.
-Huh? What do you think?

50:27.958 --> 50:28.958
-So many likes.
-[Rob] What do you think?

50:29.125 --> 50:30.125
-[Britt] It's...
-[Rob] Do it this...

50:31.750 --> 50:33.833
-[Britt] Smile, Holt.
-Not right now.

50:34.000 --> 50:35.041
[Rob] Holt can't smile.

50:35.208 --> 50:36.625
He put all his money
on the wrong horse.

50:36.791 --> 50:37.958
Okay. Can you ID the others?

50:39.125 --> 50:40.375
Are we missing anybody?

50:40.541 --> 50:42.250
[Maddox] You can see
for yourself.

50:42.416 --> 50:44.416
[indistinct chatter]

50:50.500 --> 50:51.791
[Nicole] Hey!

50:51.958 --> 50:54.125
All right,
who wants some watermelon?

50:57.583 --> 50:58.583
[Chris] All right,
if one of these did it...

50:58.750 --> 50:59.916
maybe the barbecue
gave 'em a chance

51:00.083 --> 51:01.583
to scope out the house,
find an entry point.

51:01.750 --> 51:02.791
Nobody has been
in the vicinity

51:02.958 --> 51:03.958
of the house since then.

51:04.125 --> 51:05.625
Nobody's cell phone has.

51:06.625 --> 51:07.625
Doesn't mean they haven't.

51:07.791 --> 51:09.208
The available cameras
show that...

51:09.375 --> 51:11.791
46 vehicles entered
your street between...

51:11.958 --> 51:13.958
9:00 and 10:30 this morning.

51:14.125 --> 51:15.250
None of them stopped.

51:15.416 --> 51:16.416
How about the streets behind?

51:16.583 --> 51:17.625
Someone could have come in
through the back, right?

51:17.791 --> 51:19.125
[Maddox] I processed
all available cameras...

51:19.291 --> 51:20.875
nobody entered
your neighborhood this morning

51:21.041 --> 51:23.083
who is not accounted for
with an alibi.

51:23.250 --> 51:25.083
Wait. Bill Peterson.
House behind ours.

51:25.250 --> 51:27.833
He's a bird nut. He's got
a camera out back. It's, uh...

51:29.250 --> 51:30.583
It's online. It's...

51:32.541 --> 51:34.750
I think
it's petersonsyard.com.

51:34.916 --> 51:36.458
That's it. That's my fence.

51:36.625 --> 51:37.708
I will extract the footage
from this morning

51:37.875 --> 51:39.000
from the cloud.

51:40.875 --> 51:43.375
Negative. William Peterson's
Internet provider

51:43.541 --> 51:44.791
has experienced an outage.

51:44.958 --> 51:46.791
The footage
is still archiving.

51:46.958 --> 51:48.291
This will take some time.

51:48.458 --> 51:50.541
So, nobody's been anywhere
near my house today?

51:50.708 --> 51:51.916
Correct. Not this morning.

51:54.666 --> 51:56.750
-Wait. What did you say?
-Correct. Not this morning.

51:57.416 --> 51:59.041
Okay, so who drove?

51:59.208 --> 52:00.333
The barbecue was Sunday,
2:00 p.m.

52:00.500 --> 52:02.750
Can you check who drove
their own vehicle there?

52:03.750 --> 52:05.375
[Maddox] I can identify
four vehicles

52:05.541 --> 52:07.750
registered to employees
of Viking.

52:08.625 --> 52:09.625
Robert Nelson's vehicle

52:09.791 --> 52:12.500
entered your street
at 2:30 p.m.

52:17.666 --> 52:19.583
[Chris] There's what?
Three people riding with him?

52:19.750 --> 52:21.333
Okay. I need to talk to Rob.

52:21.500 --> 52:22.541
I'm not following.

52:22.708 --> 52:23.958
Please, just get Rob
on the phone.

52:24.125 --> 52:25.583
[line ringing]

52:27.375 --> 52:28.166
-[Rob] Hello?
-Mr. Nelson,

52:28.333 --> 52:29.125
this is Judge Maddox...

52:29.291 --> 52:30.875
-in the Mercy chamber.
-Yeah, I saw the number.

52:31.041 --> 52:33.041
Hey, Rob.
Buddy, I'm on the clock.

52:33.750 --> 52:34.916
Who'd you give
a ride to on Sunday?

52:35.083 --> 52:36.625
-[Rob] To the barbecue?
-Yeah.

52:36.791 --> 52:37.791
Carla, Marie, and Leo.

52:37.958 --> 52:39.291
Okay. Did any of them
not leave with you?

52:39.458 --> 52:40.458
[Rob] None of 'em.

52:40.625 --> 52:43.208
You know, there wasn't
really a plan, so...

52:43.375 --> 52:46.000
I ended up taking home
Bill and Debra.

52:46.166 --> 52:47.041
Everybody else must
have found their own way.

52:47.208 --> 52:48.166
Got Ubers.

52:48.750 --> 52:50.625
Yeah. Yeah, that makes sense.

52:52.083 --> 52:54.625
Hey, did anybody not show up
to work yesterday?

52:54.791 --> 52:55.750
Anybody missing?

52:55.916 --> 52:57.166
Nope. No one that I know of.

52:57.333 --> 52:59.541
[Chris] Okay. All right.
Sorry, man, I gotta go.

52:59.708 --> 53:02.208
Okay. Let me know
if you need anything else.

53:03.708 --> 53:06.458
[sputters] All right.
This still could be it.

53:06.625 --> 53:08.041
[Maddox] Please, can you
clarify your meaning?

53:08.208 --> 53:09.833
Just give me a second, okay?

53:10.000 --> 53:12.166
All right, can you give me
Britt's video again?

53:12.333 --> 53:13.500
The one with the sleazebag?

53:15.291 --> 53:16.833
Mom's in her bed crying.

53:17.000 --> 53:19.125
Dad legit scared the shit
out of us yesterday.

53:19.291 --> 53:21.166
Telling you, dude's dangerous.

53:21.500 --> 53:22.541
I heard my mom
talk to her friend

53:22.708 --> 53:23.791
about getting a divorce.

53:23.958 --> 53:25.250
Really hope
she meant that shit.

53:27.500 --> 53:28.625
Shit, you hear that?

53:28.791 --> 53:30.000
I think my dad's home.
I'm out.

53:30.166 --> 53:31.166
[sleazebag] Hey, wait. Hey...

53:32.083 --> 53:33.375
When was this recorded?

53:36.625 --> 53:38.625
[Maddox] Last night
at 9:15 p.m.

53:38.791 --> 53:40.666
-I know how they did it.
-[Maddox] Mr. Raven?

53:40.833 --> 53:43.041
Access department logs. Uh...

53:43.208 --> 53:44.791
Check hours for yesterday.

53:56.083 --> 53:57.291
See, look, I wasn't home.

53:57.458 --> 53:59.166
That wasn't me.

53:59.333 --> 54:00.625
I gotta talk to Britt again.

54:00.791 --> 54:02.958
Unless juveniles were witness
to a crime being committed...

54:03.125 --> 54:04.041
That's just it,
she was a witness.

54:04.208 --> 54:05.208
Maybe not to the murder...

54:05.375 --> 54:07.333
but she saw something, okay?
I know it.

54:10.916 --> 54:12.125
[line ringing]

54:15.958 --> 54:17.291
[reporter] LAPD Detective

54:17.458 --> 54:18.458
-Chris Raven's Mercy trial...
-[Chris] Hey, Britt!

54:18.625 --> 54:20.583
-Britt, you there, kiddo?
-...has now been underway

54:20.750 --> 54:22.000
-for nearly an hour.
-[Britt] Go away.

54:22.166 --> 54:23.541
[reporter] This footage
of his arrest...

54:23.708 --> 54:25.208
What's goin' on?
Did Grandpa say something?

54:25.375 --> 54:27.500
I told you
don't listen to him, okay?

54:27.666 --> 54:29.791
-This is all a mistake.
-[Britt] You're a liar.

54:30.958 --> 54:33.958
No, Britt, I'm not lying.

54:34.125 --> 54:36.458
It's all over the web.
You were arrested at a bar.

54:36.625 --> 54:37.541
[reporter]
Ask yourselves this,

54:37.708 --> 54:38.500
is this how...

54:38.666 --> 54:41.041
-an innocent man would behave?
-You were drinking again.

54:41.500 --> 54:42.458
-Britt...
-Is that why you've been

54:42.625 --> 54:43.666
such an asshole?

54:43.833 --> 54:45.375
This whole past year?

54:47.916 --> 54:49.041
-Did you do it?
-[Chris] No.

54:50.166 --> 54:51.625
Do you hear me?
I didn't kill your mom.

54:51.791 --> 54:52.708
I swear to God.

54:52.875 --> 54:54.000
[Britt] Well, everyone
on the Internet's saying

54:54.166 --> 54:55.666
you must be guilty
if you're at Mercy.

54:55.833 --> 54:56.875
There are polls and stuff.

54:57.041 --> 54:59.083
I mean, everyone says
you must have done it.

54:59.250 --> 55:00.583
They don't know
what they're talkin' about.

55:00.750 --> 55:01.500
[knocking on door]

55:01.666 --> 55:02.625
[Jeff] Britt,
who are you talking to?

55:03.958 --> 55:05.333
-I'm going. I'm going.
-Wait, Britt, Britt, Britt.

55:05.500 --> 55:06.875
Britt, wait,
this is Judge Maddox.

55:07.041 --> 55:08.541
[Jeff] We think
you should be with us.

55:08.708 --> 55:10.666
[Maddox] Your father is
mounting his defense, Britt.

55:10.833 --> 55:12.833
-He requires your assistance.
-He killed my mom.

55:13.000 --> 55:14.375
Not necessarily.

55:14.541 --> 55:15.666
[Jeff] Britt,
are you listening?

55:15.833 --> 55:18.708
Please come out, right now.
We need you out here, please.

55:18.875 --> 55:20.333
Okay, I need a minute,
Grandpa.

55:20.500 --> 55:21.416
-[Jeff] Okay.
-Britt, last night

55:21.625 --> 55:22.625
you heard a noise
in the house.

55:22.791 --> 55:23.791
-How do you know that?
-You were online talking to...

55:23.958 --> 55:25.083
-That's my private stuff!
-[Britt] I know, hon.

55:25.250 --> 55:26.291
[Britt] No. Why are you
looking at my stuff?

55:26.458 --> 55:27.583
I know, kiddo.
I shouldn't have, honey.

55:27.750 --> 55:30.500
Okay, okay, it's not right.
I'm sorry, but...

55:30.666 --> 55:32.291
you gotta tell me,
what did you hear?

55:33.125 --> 55:35.541
Was it your mom? Did she come
downstairs or something?

55:35.708 --> 55:37.791
She was in bed, okay?

55:37.958 --> 55:38.958
It sounded like
a door closing...

55:39.125 --> 55:41.083
-but there was nobody.
-Did you hear anything else?

55:42.125 --> 55:43.125
Another noise after...

55:43.291 --> 55:45.458
but I checked the house,
and it was nothing.

55:45.625 --> 55:48.291
Then Jenna picked me up to go
stay at her place. That's it.

55:49.833 --> 55:51.750
I need her Instagram.
Secret one.

55:54.250 --> 55:55.750
[Britt] This shit is haunted.

55:55.916 --> 55:57.625
This has got to be a ghost.

55:58.333 --> 55:59.416
-Oh, my God.
-Okay, this is last night.

55:59.583 --> 56:00.375
It's so dark in here.

56:00.541 --> 56:01.375
[Chris] Britt,
you recorded it, right?

56:01.541 --> 56:02.541
You put it up
on your Instagram.

56:02.708 --> 56:04.916
You posted about
looking for a ghost?

56:05.083 --> 56:06.791
Yeah, after I heard the noise.

56:06.958 --> 56:08.500
[Britt] I mean,
it's a freaking ghost haunt,

56:08.666 --> 56:10.125
or I'm ripped off my tits.

56:10.833 --> 56:13.000
-Call Zak Bagans, guys.
-[Chris] Pause. Pause it.

56:13.708 --> 56:15.708
Britt, honey, were you
in the basement last night?

56:16.166 --> 56:17.208
[Britt] No.

56:17.375 --> 56:19.000
You sure?
And you didn't check it?

56:19.166 --> 56:20.583
[Britt] Dad, you know
I don't go down there.

56:22.625 --> 56:24.416
We always keep that
door closed. Play it again.

56:24.583 --> 56:26.000
[Britt] I mean,
it's a freaking ghost haunt,

56:26.166 --> 56:27.666
or I'm ripped off my tits.

56:27.833 --> 56:29.708
-Call Zak Bagans, guys.
-[Chris] Pause.

56:32.125 --> 56:33.125
Can you clean it up?

56:34.916 --> 56:36.166
[screen chiming]

56:40.083 --> 56:41.791
He never left.

56:42.625 --> 56:44.958
He came for the party.
Rideshared to get there.

56:45.125 --> 56:46.458
Everyone thought
he got a lift home

56:46.625 --> 56:47.875
with someone else,
but he didn't.

56:48.041 --> 56:49.208
He hid in my basement
for two days.

56:49.375 --> 56:50.458
Wait, there was someone
in the house?

56:50.625 --> 56:51.625
I gotta go, kiddo.

56:51.791 --> 56:52.916
-I love you.
-No, Dad. Who killed mom?

56:53.083 --> 56:54.041
I don't know,

56:54.208 --> 56:55.416
but I'm gonna find out
and I'll call you back...

56:55.583 --> 56:57.833
I promise, and I love you.
I love you, honey.

57:00.958 --> 57:02.125
Okay, so it looks like a man.

57:02.291 --> 57:04.416
So, we rule out the women
and the people who drove.

57:04.583 --> 57:06.541
They had to drive themselves
home from the barbecue.

57:07.875 --> 57:08.791
Why hasn't my guilt dropped?

57:08.958 --> 57:09.958
What appears to be a man
in your basement

57:10.125 --> 57:11.125
could simply be a shadow.

57:11.291 --> 57:12.458
[Chris] Oh,
for crying out loud.

57:12.625 --> 57:14.333
-[Maddox] Mr. Raven...
-I'm thinking.

57:14.500 --> 57:16.291
[Maddox] No, you're not.

57:17.625 --> 57:18.625
Excuse me?

57:18.791 --> 57:20.416
You are following
your "gut"...

57:20.583 --> 57:21.875
but processing evidence

57:22.041 --> 57:24.750
requires clear,
linear thinking.

57:24.916 --> 57:26.791
You must move from one piece
of the puzzle to the next

57:27.000 --> 57:28.583
and you have missed a step.

57:29.458 --> 57:30.791
Okay. Do you want
to enlighten me?

57:30.958 --> 57:32.875
You're looking for a suspect
of Viking Shipping...

57:33.041 --> 57:34.666
because Burke told you
about Nicole's investigation

57:34.833 --> 57:36.083
into missing chemicals.

57:36.250 --> 57:37.541
You have not addressed
that investigation.

57:37.708 --> 57:38.791
Shit. You're right.

57:39.750 --> 57:41.125
Okay, we need to get into...

57:41.291 --> 57:42.250
[Maddox] This is
the Viking Shipping

57:42.416 --> 57:43.291
internal computer server...

57:43.458 --> 57:45.375
and the search function
is available to you.

57:47.208 --> 57:49.250
Not bad.
Thank you, Your Honor.

57:50.375 --> 57:51.375
Search Nicole Raven.

57:54.416 --> 57:55.541
Let's start with the emails.

57:55.708 --> 57:57.250
Open Nicole's inbox.

57:57.791 --> 57:59.833
I'm looking for missing stock.

58:05.708 --> 58:07.000
[Chris] Wait,
what is that? "UG"?

58:07.166 --> 58:09.541
[Maddox] It most likely
refers to urea granules.

58:09.708 --> 58:11.458
Synthetic urea
appears frequently

58:11.625 --> 58:12.875
on Viking's records.

58:13.583 --> 58:15.291
[Chris] All right,
still looking.

58:18.208 --> 58:19.208
Who's "the three of us"?

58:20.958 --> 58:22.541
[Maddox] There's an email
from the sixth.

58:22.708 --> 58:24.708
[Chris] UG. Holt knew.

58:27.833 --> 58:28.833
How much was missing?

58:29.000 --> 58:30.541
[Maddox] For the past
six months...

58:30.708 --> 58:33.708
every delivery to Biobeauty
has had a discrepancy.

58:33.875 --> 58:35.458
Each shipment
has had an additional...

58:35.625 --> 58:37.833
50 kilo container
of urea granules...

58:38.000 --> 58:38.916
listed on
the delivery docket.

58:39.083 --> 58:39.958
[Chris] So, they're getting
overcharged?

58:40.125 --> 58:41.875
No. The physical order
is correct,

58:42.041 --> 58:43.875
and they're being
charged appropriately.

58:44.916 --> 58:46.166
It's only the delivery docket

58:46.333 --> 58:48.583
that lists an additional
50 kilo container.

58:48.750 --> 58:49.916
Someone's gaming
the stock records...

58:50.083 --> 58:50.958
to cover up the fact that

58:51.125 --> 58:52.500
urea granules
are going missing.

58:52.666 --> 58:54.625
Six months at maybe
six missing containers,

58:54.791 --> 58:55.541
what's that?

58:55.708 --> 58:58.083
Three hundred kilos.
What's that worth to someone?

58:58.250 --> 58:59.833
Synthetic urea is a component

59:00.000 --> 59:01.708
of several
dermatological products.

59:01.875 --> 59:04.708
It can also be used
in agricultural fertilizers...

59:04.875 --> 59:06.875
and in the production
of methamphetamine.

59:08.125 --> 59:10.791
Drug use is endemic
in Red Zones across the city.

59:10.958 --> 59:12.041
[siren blaring]

59:13.291 --> 59:15.000
There is an extremely
lucrative black market

59:15.208 --> 59:16.791
for industrial-grade urea.

59:16.958 --> 59:18.625
These are the people
who are committing crimes...

59:18.791 --> 59:21.083
and we want to separate them
from the others in society.

59:21.250 --> 59:23.458
[Chris] So if someone took it
and sold it, they made bank.

59:24.833 --> 59:26.791
Sure as hell wouldn't
want to get caught.

59:27.125 --> 59:28.041
So maybe Holt found something,

59:28.208 --> 59:29.208
didn't get a chance
to tell Nic.

59:30.500 --> 59:32.750
Open Holt's inbox.
Search Nicole Raven.

59:38.791 --> 59:41.750
Okay, this was Friday,
2:30 p.m.

59:55.333 --> 59:56.750
[Nicole] It's gone
too far already,

59:56.916 --> 59:58.208
we should just go to the cops.

59:58.375 --> 59:59.375
[Holt] I can
make things right!

59:59.541 --> 01:00:00.500
Just give me a few days.

01:00:00.666 --> 01:00:02.000
It will not be a problem.

01:00:03.791 --> 01:00:05.541
-Cool?
-No, it's not cool.

01:00:05.708 --> 01:00:06.666
[Holt] It's not
that complicated!

01:00:06.833 --> 01:00:07.791
[Nicole] It is complicated.

01:00:07.958 --> 01:00:09.500
-My job is on the line!
-[Holt grunts]

01:00:14.708 --> 01:00:16.750
[Chris] Holt's always
had a gambling problem.

01:00:17.291 --> 01:00:18.583
I need Holt's financials.

01:00:18.750 --> 01:00:19.958
Can you give me
the last six months?

01:00:20.125 --> 01:00:21.750
Bank, credit card,
anything you can.

01:00:27.958 --> 01:00:28.958
Oh, my God.

01:00:30.375 --> 01:00:32.250
Holy shit,
he's in big trouble.

01:00:37.458 --> 01:00:38.666
Rob's been bailing him out?

01:00:38.833 --> 01:00:39.750
Well, this is it.
This is it, right?

01:00:39.916 --> 01:00:40.750
I mean, we got him.

01:00:45.708 --> 01:00:46.708
You're not serious.

01:00:46.875 --> 01:00:49.208
Money is a motive,
but it's only in theory.

01:00:49.375 --> 01:00:50.708
You have
no concrete evidence...

01:00:50.875 --> 01:00:53.083
as to how Holt Charles might
have committed the crime.

01:00:53.250 --> 01:00:54.250
Let me talk to Rob.

01:00:54.791 --> 01:00:56.291
[line ringing]

01:01:03.041 --> 01:01:04.791
Holy crap, Chris!

01:01:04.958 --> 01:01:07.416
They told us you were
at that Mercy place. You okay?

01:01:07.583 --> 01:01:08.583
This is Judge Maddox.

01:01:08.750 --> 01:01:10.166
You're indeed speaking
to the Mercy Court...

01:01:10.333 --> 01:01:11.541
where Detective Raven
is standing trial

01:01:11.708 --> 01:01:13.000
for his wife's murder.

01:01:13.166 --> 01:01:14.250
[Holt] Yes, ma'am.
That's what I heard.

01:01:14.416 --> 01:01:15.500
[Maddox] I believe
Detective Raven

01:01:15.666 --> 01:01:17.333
wishes to speak
with Robert Nelson.

01:01:17.500 --> 01:01:19.416
Yeah. I'll just go find him.

01:01:19.583 --> 01:01:20.625
I was just walking by,

01:01:20.791 --> 01:01:22.125
I saw the call
open on the computer.

01:01:22.291 --> 01:01:23.958
I guess he left the app open.

01:01:24.125 --> 01:01:25.250
And, Chris...

01:01:26.041 --> 01:01:27.041
Good luck, pal.

01:01:27.541 --> 01:01:28.541
Gimme a second.

01:01:30.458 --> 01:01:31.708
[softly] Son of a bitch.

01:01:31.875 --> 01:01:33.666
[Holt] Hey, Fred, can you
drive me around the yard?

01:01:34.708 --> 01:01:35.791
[Maddox] If he is involved,
he may flee,

01:01:35.958 --> 01:01:37.000
and time is very short.

01:01:37.166 --> 01:01:38.166
All right.

01:01:39.416 --> 01:01:40.208
We're gonna have
to make him talk.

01:01:40.375 --> 01:01:41.166
Jaq's gonna have
to make him talk.

01:01:41.333 --> 01:01:42.333
Where is she?

01:01:42.750 --> 01:01:45.583
Detective Diallo
is four minutes away.

01:01:48.500 --> 01:01:50.625
[Chris] Maddox, can you track
where he was this morning?

01:01:50.791 --> 01:01:52.958
[Maddox] I am having trouble
verifying a clear alibi...

01:01:53.125 --> 01:01:55.250
from his whereabouts
at the time of the murder.

01:01:56.083 --> 01:01:58.583
I'm tracking his phone in case
he does attempt to flee.

01:01:58.750 --> 01:02:00.083
[Chris] Okay, good.
Hey, do you have a status

01:02:00.250 --> 01:02:01.625
on Peterson's
bird cam footage?

01:02:01.791 --> 01:02:02.666
I mean,
if he was at the house,

01:02:02.833 --> 01:02:03.666
the camera
might've caught him.

01:02:03.833 --> 01:02:04.833
[Maddox] Loading.

01:02:06.375 --> 01:02:07.375
Almost there.

01:02:07.541 --> 01:02:09.666
Yo, any idea where Rob's at?

01:02:10.875 --> 01:02:11.958
[Maddox] I have
this morning's footage

01:02:12.125 --> 01:02:13.833
from Bill Peterson's
bird camera.

01:02:15.291 --> 01:02:16.291
I'm afraid there's nothing.

01:02:16.458 --> 01:02:17.583
What? Nothing?

01:02:17.750 --> 01:02:19.500
All right, just show me.
Slower.

01:02:24.416 --> 01:02:25.916
Slower. Slower.

01:02:27.291 --> 01:02:29.333
Wait, what? What's this one?
The timing's right.

01:02:29.875 --> 01:02:31.625
[Maddox] The camera
was motion activated at...

01:02:31.791 --> 01:02:33.833
10:08 a.m.

01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:35.250
God damn it, is that...
That's all?

01:02:35.416 --> 01:02:37.208
The camera was not
triggered again until...

01:02:37.375 --> 01:02:38.958
11:43 a.m.

01:02:39.125 --> 01:02:40.875
All right, well,
he still had to get out.

01:02:41.041 --> 01:02:42.041
Did Bill go anywhere today?

01:02:42.541 --> 01:02:43.541
[Maddox] Phone tracking shows

01:02:43.708 --> 01:02:45.875
that Bill Peterson
left his home at...

01:02:46.041 --> 01:02:47.833
11:23 this morning.

01:02:49.333 --> 01:02:51.166
The Internet outage
in Bill Peterson's grid...

01:02:51.333 --> 01:02:54.000
affected traffic cameras
in that area, too.

01:02:54.166 --> 01:02:55.625
We will have to wait
for them to update.

01:02:55.791 --> 01:02:57.458
Hey, Chris, you there, man?

01:02:57.958 --> 01:02:58.958
I said I needed Rob.

01:02:59.125 --> 01:03:01.250
Yeah, I wasn't
able to find him.

01:03:01.416 --> 01:03:02.458
[Chris] Quit stalling.

01:03:02.625 --> 01:03:04.208
Whoa, I'm not stalling, man.
Chill.

01:03:04.375 --> 01:03:05.916
[Chris] Bullshit.
I was gonna ask...

01:03:06.083 --> 01:03:07.916
Rob to keep you there,
but the cavalry is about to...

01:03:08.083 --> 01:03:09.541
-break your goddamn door down.
-What?

01:03:09.708 --> 01:03:11.166
[Chris] I know about
the missing chemicals.

01:03:11.333 --> 01:03:12.875
I know about the hole
you're in with the bank.

01:03:13.041 --> 01:03:13.958
You stole product...

01:03:14.125 --> 01:03:15.000
and you murdered Nic
so she couldn't talk.

01:03:15.166 --> 01:03:16.041
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
I didn't hurt anyone, man.

01:03:16.208 --> 01:03:17.500
This is nuts.
I was just trying to help him.

01:03:17.666 --> 01:03:19.791
-I owed him one.
-Owed... who, what?

01:03:23.208 --> 01:03:24.833
Holt, what are you
talking about?

01:03:29.333 --> 01:03:30.541
-Holt!
-Rob, okay?

01:03:30.708 --> 01:03:31.875
I owed Rob.

01:03:34.750 --> 01:03:36.083
-What?
-Me and Nic found out...

01:03:36.250 --> 01:03:37.666
he was making
product disappear.

01:03:38.166 --> 01:03:39.083
And, I mean, shit, we all know

01:03:39.250 --> 01:03:40.791
what the stuff that comes
through here is worth...

01:03:40.958 --> 01:03:42.291
but he's been good to me, man.

01:03:42.458 --> 01:03:43.458
To all of us.

01:03:43.625 --> 01:03:45.208
Hell, he's your sponsor,
for Christ's sake.

01:03:45.375 --> 01:03:46.708
[Chris] Where is he?

01:03:46.875 --> 01:03:47.958
I don't know, dude.

01:03:48.125 --> 01:03:49.875
-I can't find him.
-Holt, where is he?

01:03:50.041 --> 01:03:51.791
[breathing heavily]

01:03:51.958 --> 01:03:54.916
Carly said he took off
in one of the trucks, okay?

01:03:55.583 --> 01:03:56.583
He just got back
from a sick day...

01:03:56.750 --> 01:03:57.958
she figured
he wasn't feeling good...

01:03:58.125 --> 01:04:00.125
-and he left. But...
-Wait, Rob was off yesterday?

01:04:00.291 --> 01:04:01.583
Yeah. He didn't come in

01:04:01.750 --> 01:04:03.583
until he was done
at the port this morning.

01:04:04.416 --> 01:04:06.083
Last time I saw him
was at your place on Sunday...

01:04:06.250 --> 01:04:07.541
and he said he wanted
to talk to Nic

01:04:07.708 --> 01:04:08.916
the way he talked to me.

01:04:09.083 --> 01:04:10.541
Let her know it was all gonna
be cool, you know?

01:04:10.708 --> 01:04:13.750
But... wanted to do it
after everyone else left.

01:04:13.916 --> 01:04:15.875
Even got me to drive
his car home for him...

01:04:16.041 --> 01:04:18.875
so the folks he gave a ride to
weren't left waiting.

01:04:19.333 --> 01:04:21.000
He stayed on,
and you drove his car?

01:04:21.500 --> 01:04:22.625
Yeah. Like I said.

01:04:22.791 --> 01:04:23.875
Son of a bitch.

01:04:24.041 --> 01:04:26.125
[Holt] I tried talking to him
at your place the weekend...

01:04:26.291 --> 01:04:27.625
Viking trucks are all tracked?

01:04:31.875 --> 01:04:32.875
Okay. Uh...

01:04:33.041 --> 01:04:34.833
There. That one.
The one in Los Feliz.

01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:36.041
[Maddox] That is Robert
Nelson's home address.

01:04:36.208 --> 01:04:37.208
The truck is not moving.

01:04:37.375 --> 01:04:38.500
Jaq, are you hearing me?

01:04:39.291 --> 01:04:41.041
-I'm touching down at Viking.
-[Chris] No, scratch that.

01:04:41.208 --> 01:04:43.458
You need to get
to 698 Tracy Street.

01:04:43.625 --> 01:04:45.208
We're going after Rob Nelson.

01:04:45.375 --> 01:04:46.791
Your Rob?

01:04:46.958 --> 01:04:48.250
All right, I'm on my way.

01:04:48.416 --> 01:04:49.541
SWAT unit four,

01:04:49.708 --> 01:04:51.583
head over
to 698 Tracy Street...

01:04:51.750 --> 01:04:52.958
-stat.
-[SWAT 1] Roger that.

01:04:53.125 --> 01:04:54.375
Local units
and the nearest patrolling

01:04:54.541 --> 01:04:55.708
SWAT team have been alerted

01:04:55.875 --> 01:04:57.125
I helped Rob
get a gun license last year.

01:04:57.291 --> 01:04:58.125
He's got weapons at the house.

01:04:58.291 --> 01:04:59.500
[Maddox] The footage
of Bill Peterson's

01:04:59.666 --> 01:05:00.791
car journey has buffered.

01:05:00.958 --> 01:05:02.958
[intriguing music playing]

01:05:27.166 --> 01:05:28.125
What, still?

01:05:28.291 --> 01:05:30.041
In the absence of new,
verifiable facts...

01:05:30.208 --> 01:05:31.750
your guilt is holding
above the threshold.

01:05:31.916 --> 01:05:33.291
Do you honestly think
that I killed Nic?

01:05:33.458 --> 01:05:34.458
The facts are all that
I'm permitted...

01:05:34.625 --> 01:05:36.625
-to consider.
-Come on. What's your gut say?

01:05:36.791 --> 01:05:37.791
I do not function that way.

01:05:37.958 --> 01:05:39.041
What about
what you said to Britt?

01:05:39.208 --> 01:05:41.208
You told her that
maybe I didn't kill Nic.

01:05:41.375 --> 01:05:42.416
-You remember?
-No, I was merely

01:05:42.583 --> 01:05:43.708
-acknowledging the...
-Bullshit!

01:05:43.875 --> 01:05:45.166
I'm just asking,
what do you think?

01:05:45.333 --> 01:05:46.541
[distorted] I cannot...
I'm not...

01:05:47.333 --> 01:05:49.250
I'm not supposed to...

01:05:50.208 --> 01:05:51.375
[normal voice] This is
the Mercy Capital Court.

01:05:51.541 --> 01:05:52.500
I'm Judge Maddox,

01:05:52.666 --> 01:05:53.708
and I'm going
to preside over your...

01:05:53.875 --> 01:05:54.916
...court, I'm Judge Maddox...

01:05:55.083 --> 01:05:56.166
and I'm going
to preside over your...

01:05:56.333 --> 01:05:57.333
-You all right?
-I am.

01:05:57.750 --> 01:05:59.041
I'm functioning
within normal parameters.

01:05:59.166 --> 01:06:00.250
Thank you.

01:06:00.416 --> 01:06:01.833
Okay.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:03.958
Let's just
put a pin in that one.

01:06:06.625 --> 01:06:07.541
This is Ten-David,
Lieutenant Vogel.

01:06:07.708 --> 01:06:08.666
We're en route to your lead.

01:06:08.833 --> 01:06:10.000
All right, Dan,
I'm glad it's you.

01:06:10.166 --> 01:06:11.125
Chris, we're about
a minute out.

01:06:11.291 --> 01:06:12.166
What do you got us
getting into?

01:06:12.333 --> 01:06:14.541
I've identified a suspect
in my wife's murder.

01:06:14.708 --> 01:06:16.125
Robert Nelson.

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:18.333
He owns an AR-15,

01:06:18.500 --> 01:06:19.916
and a semi compact
nine-millimeter.

01:06:20.083 --> 01:06:21.083
Roger that.

01:06:21.250 --> 01:06:23.291
All right, guys,
we're en route to location.

01:06:23.458 --> 01:06:26.083
Suspect armed with an AR-15.

01:06:26.250 --> 01:06:27.916
Go, go, go!

01:06:29.208 --> 01:06:30.958
[over megaphone]
Occupant of 698...

01:06:31.125 --> 01:06:32.291
this is Lieutenant Vogel

01:06:32.458 --> 01:06:34.000
with the Los Angeles
Police Department.

01:06:34.166 --> 01:06:36.666
Exit the residence
or we will make entry.

01:06:40.041 --> 01:06:41.083
All right, Chris,
we're going in.

01:06:41.916 --> 01:06:43.208
Diallo, touching down.

01:06:45.083 --> 01:06:47.250
[Dan] Never late for
the action, huh, Jaq?

01:06:48.916 --> 01:06:49.958
LAPD!
We have a search warrant.

01:06:50.125 --> 01:06:51.208
Open the door!

01:06:55.041 --> 01:06:56.291
We made entry, Jaq.

01:06:57.125 --> 01:06:58.916
Give me two in the bedroom!
Give me two in the bedroom!

01:06:59.083 --> 01:07:00.083
Lock it down!

01:07:00.250 --> 01:07:01.875
LAPD, we have
a search warrant!

01:07:02.083 --> 01:07:03.500
Living room, clear!
Move, move!

01:07:03.666 --> 01:07:04.750
Give me some people
in the backyard.

01:07:04.916 --> 01:07:06.541
-[SWAT 2] Kitchen, clear!
-[Dan] Let's go!

01:07:07.166 --> 01:07:09.041
-He's not there.
-[SWAT 3] Spread out!

01:07:09.208 --> 01:07:10.291
[Chris] And where's
the damn truck?

01:07:10.458 --> 01:07:11.875
The vehicle's GPS
is at the house.

01:07:12.041 --> 01:07:13.666
Yeah, 'cause he took it off.

01:07:13.833 --> 01:07:15.375
-Can you scan traffic cameras?
-[Maddox] I already am.

01:07:15.541 --> 01:07:16.875
The license plates
of the trucks...

01:07:17.041 --> 01:07:19.000
are not being detected
by any cameras in the city.

01:07:19.166 --> 01:07:20.458
[Chris] He probably
ditched 'em.

01:07:20.625 --> 01:07:22.333
Jaq, I need you
to put out an APB

01:07:22.500 --> 01:07:24.291
on a Viking Shipping Truck.

01:07:24.458 --> 01:07:26.125
-Can we track it?
-No, we gotta go old school.

01:07:26.291 --> 01:07:28.958
All units, be on the lookout
for a Viking Shipping Truck.

01:07:29.125 --> 01:07:30.250
Could be anywhere in the city.

01:07:30.416 --> 01:07:32.041
[Dan] Chris, there's nobody
in the house. It's empty.

01:07:32.208 --> 01:07:34.625
Just a bunch of hoarded crap
and memory lane stuff.

01:07:34.791 --> 01:07:36.291
Wait, wait, wait.
Bring that back.

01:07:36.458 --> 01:07:37.833
Stop. Stop right there.

01:07:38.000 --> 01:07:38.958
What's that picture
on the right?

01:07:39.125 --> 01:07:41.208
[Maddox] Robert Nelson was
raised in a children's home.

01:07:41.375 --> 01:07:43.083
His records were lost
in a data hack...

01:07:43.250 --> 01:07:46.375
but this image most likely
dates from that time.

01:07:46.541 --> 01:07:47.583
[Chris] Can you pull that out?

01:07:53.083 --> 01:07:53.791
Look at his arm.

01:07:53.958 --> 01:07:54.666
There's someone else
in that picture with him.

01:07:54.833 --> 01:07:56.333
Can you cross reference
and find a match?

01:07:57.125 --> 01:07:58.416
[Maddox] Searching
for a match.

01:07:58.583 --> 01:08:00.208
This may take a few minutes.

01:08:01.291 --> 01:08:03.083
[Chris] Can you pull any
cameras from earlier today?

01:08:08.500 --> 01:08:10.250
Vogel, get outside.
Check the garage.

01:08:10.416 --> 01:08:12.208
[Dan] Roger that, Chris.
Jaq, did you get that?

01:08:12.375 --> 01:08:13.375
We're out back.

01:08:13.541 --> 01:08:14.541
Initiate.

01:08:16.416 --> 01:08:18.000
-Move, move, move!
-[SWAT 3] All right, move in.

01:08:18.166 --> 01:08:19.458
-Go! Go!
-[SWAT 2] Go, go! Go!

01:08:20.875 --> 01:08:22.083
-[SWAT 4] Corners clear.
-[SWAT 5] What we got here?

01:08:22.250 --> 01:08:23.666
[SWAT 6] Active fire.
Active fire.

01:08:31.333 --> 01:08:32.333
[SWAT 7] Ten-David, clear.

01:08:35.083 --> 01:08:35.958
[Dan] Looks like
he's been planning

01:08:36.125 --> 01:08:37.041
something for a while.

01:08:38.250 --> 01:08:39.416
He's burned all the evidence.

01:08:39.583 --> 01:08:41.666
He's cutting and running
with the chemicals, right?

01:08:41.833 --> 01:08:43.000
There's gotta
be a good reason.

01:08:43.166 --> 01:08:44.541
One last payday? Selling them?

01:08:44.708 --> 01:08:45.708
There are four known

01:08:45.875 --> 01:08:47.833
Red Zone drug lab operations
in the city.

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:48.958
No, he'll never get that rig
in the Red Zone.

01:08:49.125 --> 01:08:50.083
He'll get mobbed.

01:08:51.708 --> 01:08:52.541
What if he cooked
the drugs already

01:08:52.708 --> 01:08:53.625
and he's hauling
finished product?

01:08:53.791 --> 01:08:55.500
If he has
manufactured product...

01:08:55.666 --> 01:08:57.958
the estimated street value
would be in excess of...

01:08:58.125 --> 01:08:59.208
16 million dollars.

01:08:59.375 --> 01:09:01.333
I mean, could he have?
Could he have? He made drugs?

01:09:01.958 --> 01:09:03.250
Rob Nelson achieved
a master's degree

01:09:03.416 --> 01:09:04.791
in electrical engineering.

01:09:04.958 --> 01:09:06.375
There are potentially
transferable skills

01:09:06.541 --> 01:09:07.875
from that to chemistry.

01:09:08.041 --> 01:09:09.583
Yeah, we gotta figure he's
headin' to a supply meeting.

01:09:09.750 --> 01:09:11.083
Take the cash, disappear.

01:09:15.083 --> 01:09:16.166
Hey, Jaq, can you go back?

01:09:16.333 --> 01:09:17.458
Go back.

01:09:20.208 --> 01:09:22.000
See that? He wasn't at Viking
last time we called him.

01:09:22.166 --> 01:09:23.166
He was already here.

01:09:26.166 --> 01:09:27.375
What, to your house?
To the barbecue?

01:09:27.541 --> 01:09:29.541
Hey, Lieutenant,
take a look at this.

01:09:30.166 --> 01:09:30.916
Carla, Marie, and Leo.

01:09:31.083 --> 01:09:31.875
[Dan] Chris, we might
have something here.

01:09:32.041 --> 01:09:33.375
[SWAT 8] Some kinda
chemical in here.

01:09:33.541 --> 01:09:34.375
[camera clicks]

01:09:36.833 --> 01:09:38.666
Those contained urea granules.

01:09:38.833 --> 01:09:40.458
So he was cooking product.

01:09:40.625 --> 01:09:42.291
-[objects clattering]
-Holy shit.

01:09:43.125 --> 01:09:44.625
Chris, what the hell?

01:09:45.125 --> 01:09:47.125
[Chris] See that? He took
the plates off the truck.

01:09:47.833 --> 01:09:49.875
It was all here, hidden away.

01:09:50.041 --> 01:09:51.541
He's completely offline,
no digital trail.

01:09:51.708 --> 01:09:52.625
No wonder you missed it,
Maddox.

01:09:52.791 --> 01:09:53.916
[Dan] Some sort of handbook.

01:09:55.083 --> 01:09:56.083
[SWAT 2] Checking it out.

01:09:56.583 --> 01:09:57.541
[Chris] And what
are we looking at?

01:09:57.708 --> 01:09:58.750
This is
a terrorist's handbook.

01:09:58.916 --> 01:10:00.000
-What?
-[Maddox] Urea can be combined

01:10:00.166 --> 01:10:01.083
with nitric acid...

01:10:01.250 --> 01:10:02.625
to produce urea nitrate...

01:10:02.791 --> 01:10:04.333
which is an extremely
high explosive.

01:10:14.875 --> 01:10:16.500
[Chris] Viking ships
nitric too.

01:10:16.666 --> 01:10:18.208
It was all there for him.

01:10:19.083 --> 01:10:20.541
He's made a bomb.

01:10:22.916 --> 01:10:24.000
Dan, he's got a bomb
in that truck.

01:10:24.166 --> 01:10:25.416
We need to know
what his target is.

01:10:25.583 --> 01:10:27.666
[Dan] All right, guys.
Drop it, toss everything,

01:10:27.833 --> 01:10:29.000
look for a target.

01:10:29.166 --> 01:10:30.375
Shit just got real, Jaq.

01:10:30.541 --> 01:10:31.916
Chris, I have it.

01:10:32.083 --> 01:10:33.083
[Jaq] Dan,
I'm going after our sub.

01:10:33.250 --> 01:10:34.291
[Dan] Roger that.

01:10:34.458 --> 01:10:36.125
[Chris] How much explosives
is he carrying?

01:10:36.750 --> 01:10:37.708
[Maddox] Based
on the ride height,

01:10:37.875 --> 01:10:38.750
the load on the suspension...

01:10:38.916 --> 01:10:41.208
appears to weigh
in excess of 3,000 pounds.

01:10:42.625 --> 01:10:43.958
[Chris] All right. Where's
he going in that thing?

01:10:44.125 --> 01:10:46.958
[Maddox] He's heading south
on the 101 towards Downtown.

01:10:47.750 --> 01:10:49.000
[Chris] Wait,
did he just speed up?

01:10:49.166 --> 01:10:50.333
[Maddox] His speed
is increasing.

01:10:50.500 --> 01:10:52.750
Sixty... 70 miles per hour.

01:10:52.916 --> 01:10:54.958
He will reach Downtown
in three minutes.

01:10:55.125 --> 01:10:56.250
Chris, I have a match.

01:10:57.625 --> 01:10:58.833
[Chris] Can you find out
who that is?

01:11:06.083 --> 01:11:07.375
Wait.

01:11:07.541 --> 01:11:08.583
David Webb?

01:11:21.625 --> 01:11:24.041
[Maddox] David Webb was taken
into care of child services...

01:11:24.208 --> 01:11:25.541
along with
his older brother...

01:11:25.708 --> 01:11:27.083
Robert Webb.

01:11:27.250 --> 01:11:29.541
But they were parted
when Robert was adopted alone.

01:11:31.166 --> 01:11:33.958
They changed Rob's name when
he was adopted by the Nelsons.

01:11:34.125 --> 01:11:36.583
Meeting me at AA,
sponsoring me...

01:11:36.750 --> 01:11:38.458
it all came after
the Webb trial.

01:11:39.500 --> 01:11:43.125
This was never about Nic.
It was about me and you.

01:11:43.291 --> 01:11:44.625
His target is the Mercy Court.

01:11:44.791 --> 01:11:46.541
Jaq, his target is Mercy.

01:11:46.708 --> 01:11:49.708
He's doin' it for revenge.
Rob is David Webb's brother.

01:11:49.875 --> 01:11:50.875
[Jaq] What?

01:11:51.041 --> 01:11:53.416
I processed
Webb myself, Chris.

01:11:56.791 --> 01:11:58.291
[Maddox] I'm detecting
a second heat signature

01:11:58.458 --> 01:11:59.833
in the cabin of the truck.

01:12:00.000 --> 01:12:02.250
Sending in a drone
for visual confirmation.

01:12:02.416 --> 01:12:04.416
-[drone whirring]
-[imperceptible]

01:12:04.583 --> 01:12:05.916
Did he just talk to someone?

01:12:06.083 --> 01:12:08.541
If he speaks again,
I'll attempt to decipher it.

01:12:11.375 --> 01:12:12.541
[imperceptible]

01:12:15.000 --> 01:12:16.000
Who the hell is that?

01:12:16.958 --> 01:12:19.666
I'm back tracing the truck's
route before we acquired it.

01:12:22.541 --> 01:12:24.708
Wait. Can I talk
to Britt quick?

01:12:26.791 --> 01:12:28.208
Please, Maddox.

01:12:34.708 --> 01:12:36.125
-[Jeff] Hello.
-[Chris] Jeff, put Britt on.

01:12:36.291 --> 01:12:37.416
[Jeff] You had your chance
to talk to her, Chris.

01:12:37.583 --> 01:12:38.916
-You'll never get another one.
-I didn't do it, Jeff.

01:12:39.083 --> 01:12:41.125
-I'm not gonna listen to this!
-And I've got the guy who did.

01:12:41.291 --> 01:12:42.666
Did you hear me?
I didn't do it.

01:12:42.833 --> 01:12:44.916
-[Jeff] Wait, you mean...
-Now put Britt on.

01:12:45.083 --> 01:12:46.083
[Jeff] Uh...

01:12:46.583 --> 01:12:49.208
She went out front
to get some air, I guess.

01:12:50.041 --> 01:12:51.041
I'll be back in a sec.

01:12:51.750 --> 01:12:54.583
Maddox, pull up
Jeff's doorbell camera.

01:12:57.958 --> 01:12:59.041
[Chris shudders]

01:12:59.208 --> 01:13:01.833
No. No way.

01:13:02.000 --> 01:13:03.208
No, he wouldn't.

01:13:03.375 --> 01:13:04.416
-[Britt] No! What are...
-[Rob] Just take...

01:13:04.583 --> 01:13:05.666
-[Chris] No.
-[Britt] Grandpa!

01:13:06.166 --> 01:13:09.250
-[Britt screaming]
-[Chris] No, no way. No.

01:13:09.833 --> 01:13:11.541
Jaq, it's Britt.

01:13:11.708 --> 01:13:13.625
Get in the air,
you gotta get on that truck.

01:13:14.916 --> 01:13:17.125
[SWAT 2] Jaq, we got a timer!

01:13:18.125 --> 01:13:19.125
[Chris] Dan, get out!
Get outta there!

01:13:19.291 --> 01:13:20.666
[Dan] Avalanche!
Avalanche! Avalanche!

01:13:20.833 --> 01:13:22.083
[Jaq] Get the hell
outta there.

01:13:22.250 --> 01:13:23.833
Everyone, move!
Get outta there!

01:13:24.000 --> 01:13:25.416
Now, now, get out!

01:13:30.125 --> 01:13:31.750
[officers screaming]

01:13:37.208 --> 01:13:38.000
[officer] Put it out,
put it out!

01:13:38.166 --> 01:13:38.958
[Chris] Jaq?

01:13:39.125 --> 01:13:40.166
[Chris panting]

01:13:41.916 --> 01:13:43.291
Jaq, Jaq?

01:13:44.166 --> 01:13:45.000
Jaq?

01:13:47.541 --> 01:13:49.125
Could that have been it?

01:13:49.291 --> 01:13:50.625
Could that have been the bomb?

01:13:51.916 --> 01:13:53.125
Maddox?

01:13:53.291 --> 01:13:55.458
That was only a small volume
of the explosive materials...

01:13:55.625 --> 01:13:57.041
that he likely had available.

01:13:57.791 --> 01:13:58.875
If he detonates...

01:14:01.875 --> 01:14:04.833
fatalities could number
in the thousands.

01:14:06.458 --> 01:14:07.750
[Jaq] Oh, my God.

01:14:08.708 --> 01:14:09.708
Jaq, you okay?

01:14:10.583 --> 01:14:12.291
Yeah, yeah, I'm okay, Chris.

01:14:13.250 --> 01:14:14.833
The SWAT team, Vogel...

01:14:15.666 --> 01:14:16.625
We can't let him

01:14:16.791 --> 01:14:17.625
-get away with this.
-I know.

01:14:17.791 --> 01:14:19.250
[Jaq] He's gonna pay.

01:14:19.416 --> 01:14:21.541
I'm sorry, but you gotta move.

01:14:21.708 --> 01:14:23.708
Get after that truck.
We gotta stop him.

01:14:30.166 --> 01:14:31.708
[Maddox] I will stop the trial
immediately... and the chair

01:14:31.875 --> 01:14:33.125
-will release you.
-Wait. No, no.

01:14:33.291 --> 01:14:34.250
-I have to.
-[Chris] You stop the trial,

01:14:34.416 --> 01:14:35.250
we cut off.

01:14:35.416 --> 01:14:36.833
Right? We lose cloud access?

01:14:37.000 --> 01:14:38.291
-Yes, correct.
-[Chris] No.

01:14:38.458 --> 01:14:39.416
No way.
We gotta stop Rob first.

01:14:39.583 --> 01:14:41.166
-I'm staying in the chair.
-The SWAT team are all dead.

01:14:41.333 --> 01:14:42.583
If the SWAT team are dead...

01:14:42.750 --> 01:14:43.833
and Nic is dead,

01:14:44.000 --> 01:14:45.625
and if Rob gets away
with whatever he's planned...

01:14:45.791 --> 01:14:47.958
then they will all have
died for nothing.

01:14:49.083 --> 01:14:51.166
-The rules of this court...
-To hell with the rules.

01:14:51.333 --> 01:14:52.750
-No. I cannot... No!
-Break 'em. Bend 'em!

01:14:52.916 --> 01:14:55.833
And if you stay in that chair,
you're going to be executed.

01:14:59.125 --> 01:15:00.416
Everything you deduced...

01:15:01.708 --> 01:15:02.708
The facts...

01:15:03.791 --> 01:15:05.000
made it appear impossible.

01:15:05.166 --> 01:15:06.166
[distorted] Impossible.

01:15:06.333 --> 01:15:09.083
[normal voice] Your...
gut instincts were...

01:15:10.916 --> 01:15:12.291
-right.
-[Chris] Yeah, I was right.

01:15:12.458 --> 01:15:13.583
[Maddox] What if I...
failed them?

01:15:13.750 --> 01:15:14.750
If you failed any of them,

01:15:14.916 --> 01:15:16.583
then I guess
we're in the same boat.

01:15:16.750 --> 01:15:18.250
Turns out I've failed
the people I love the most.

01:15:18.416 --> 01:15:21.291
I've been a deadbeat husband,
a lousy father...

01:15:21.458 --> 01:15:22.750
So, it looks like we both
need to accept the fact

01:15:22.916 --> 01:15:24.416
that we failed people.

01:15:24.583 --> 01:15:27.208
But we've got this one chance
to make up for it.

01:15:27.375 --> 01:15:29.166
We can make up for it
by stopping Rob

01:15:29.333 --> 01:15:31.208
from hurting anybody else.

01:15:31.375 --> 01:15:33.625
And we need to stop him,
the same way we found him.

01:15:34.833 --> 01:15:35.958
Together.

01:15:39.000 --> 01:15:40.000
Okay.

01:15:41.125 --> 01:15:42.333
LAPD units are in position.

01:15:42.500 --> 01:15:44.708
[reporter] The stolen big rig
here now on the highway,

01:15:44.875 --> 01:15:46.208
you can see it. Looks like...

01:15:46.416 --> 01:15:47.958
[operator] Suspect
is exiting the 101.

01:15:48.125 --> 01:15:50.291
[Chris] Jaq, we gotta
get him out of Downtown.

01:15:50.458 --> 01:15:51.291
It's too populated.

01:15:51.458 --> 01:15:54.041
[Jaq] Yeah, well, I'm all open
to ideas here, Chris.

01:15:55.375 --> 01:15:56.750
[officer] We've got units
in place at the off-ramp

01:15:56.916 --> 01:15:58.208
ready to intercept.

01:15:58.375 --> 01:15:59.333
[truck horn blaring]

01:15:59.500 --> 01:16:00.500
Oh, shit!

01:16:02.500 --> 01:16:03.708
-What can I do to help?
-Can you bring up the map...

01:16:03.875 --> 01:16:05.541
so we can track his route?

01:16:05.708 --> 01:16:06.708
Now!

01:16:06.875 --> 01:16:08.416
[Maddox] If his target
is the Mercy Court...

01:16:08.583 --> 01:16:10.291
we will not have
much time to stop him

01:16:10.458 --> 01:16:12.250
before he reaches
the Mercy building.

01:16:12.416 --> 01:16:14.875
[Chris] Okay, I need tactical.
Get Havelock on the line.

01:16:15.875 --> 01:16:17.416
Hold back! Goddamn it!

01:16:17.583 --> 01:16:18.583
[officer 2] I'm tailing him.

01:16:18.750 --> 01:16:19.791
Backup's just arrived
on the scene.

01:16:30.583 --> 01:16:32.500
[Maddox] Captain Havelock with
tactical has been notified.

01:16:33.166 --> 01:16:34.041
We will establish

01:16:34.208 --> 01:16:35.541
a communication line
with him shortly.

01:16:36.875 --> 01:16:38.208
We're gonna go live to
our news chopper right now...

01:16:38.375 --> 01:16:39.583
give us some more information

01:16:39.750 --> 01:16:41.583
and a better perspective
of this chase...

01:16:41.750 --> 01:16:43.708
that's going on through
Downtown, Los Angeles.

01:16:43.875 --> 01:16:45.291
-[helicopter whirring]
-[siren blaring]

01:16:46.250 --> 01:16:47.583
[news anchor] Police say
it is very dangerous.

01:16:47.750 --> 01:16:51.250
It is being chased
by several LAPD squad cars.

01:16:51.416 --> 01:16:53.250
-[truck horn blaring]
-[people screaming]

01:16:58.208 --> 01:16:59.291
[news anchor] Okay,
we are warning people

01:16:59.458 --> 01:17:00.541
to not go outside...

01:17:00.708 --> 01:17:02.833
and try and take pictures
of this chase.

01:17:03.708 --> 01:17:06.625
Devastating situation
right now on Grand Avenue.

01:17:06.791 --> 01:17:08.333
[sirens blaring]

01:17:11.208 --> 01:17:12.708
[people screaming]

01:17:13.916 --> 01:17:14.833
[Maddox] Chris,
you're live with Havelock.

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:15.833
[Jaq] Go ahead, Havelock.

01:17:17.208 --> 01:17:19.000
This is Captain Havelock
with tactical.

01:17:19.166 --> 01:17:20.416
If you push him east
on 6th Street,

01:17:20.583 --> 01:17:22.458
I can have a blockade
set up in five.

01:17:22.625 --> 01:17:23.666
It's far enough
out of Downtown...

01:17:23.833 --> 01:17:26.125
that we could try to stop him
and retrieve the hostage.

01:17:26.291 --> 01:17:27.208
We'll have units
surrounding him

01:17:27.375 --> 01:17:28.333
at the end of the bridge.

01:17:28.500 --> 01:17:29.583
SWAT will come in
with a helicopter

01:17:29.750 --> 01:17:30.958
to get your daughter out.

01:17:33.500 --> 01:17:34.625
[Jaq] Chris?

01:17:34.791 --> 01:17:35.791
Do it.

01:17:35.958 --> 01:17:37.875
Diallo to all units,
I need you code 100...

01:17:38.041 --> 01:17:40.250
on the intersection
of South Grand and 6th Street.

01:17:40.416 --> 01:17:42.750
Cut his options.
Force him east on 6th.

01:17:45.333 --> 01:17:47.458
[truck horn blaring]

01:17:50.125 --> 01:17:51.541
[Chris] All right. We got him.
He's going for it.

01:17:51.708 --> 01:17:52.666
[Jaq] Havelock,
I hope you're ready

01:17:52.833 --> 01:17:53.750
'cause we're sending him
your way.

01:17:55.333 --> 01:17:56.583
[Havelock] All set here,
Diallo.

01:17:56.750 --> 01:17:58.166
As long as he stays on 6th...

01:17:58.333 --> 01:17:59.708
you'll lead him
straight to us.

01:17:59.875 --> 01:18:00.875
[Jaq] Roger that.

01:18:01.041 --> 01:18:03.333
All units, keep him on 6th.
Do not let him turn off.

01:18:03.500 --> 01:18:05.791
Prepare to initiate plan A
on my command.

01:18:05.958 --> 01:18:07.000
[officer] Control,
suspect is now heading

01:18:07.166 --> 01:18:09.375
towards the Viaduct Bridge.
Over.

01:18:09.541 --> 01:18:12.500
[Maddox] Chris,
the SWAT team is arriving.

01:18:14.000 --> 01:18:15.750
[news anchor 2] Very dangerous
situation here.

01:18:15.958 --> 01:18:17.083
We're looking at a...

01:18:17.250 --> 01:18:19.083
[officer 2] Aerial unit
is in pursuit.

01:18:19.250 --> 01:18:20.416
[Jaq] Havelock, are you ready?

01:18:20.583 --> 01:18:21.583
[Havelock] Affirmative.

01:18:21.750 --> 01:18:23.666
Tactical is clear
to begin rescue operations...

01:18:23.833 --> 01:18:25.000
as soon as he reaches
the viaduct.

01:18:25.166 --> 01:18:26.833
We'll have 60 seconds
before he clears the bridge.

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:29.208
[news anchor] Okay, he's being
directed towards the bridge.

01:18:29.375 --> 01:18:30.541
Take a look at this. Wow.

01:18:30.708 --> 01:18:32.916
Okay, SWAT officers
are now on the scene.

01:18:33.083 --> 01:18:34.083
They are dropping in...

01:18:34.250 --> 01:18:35.625
[Havelock] Easy does it, boys.

01:18:35.791 --> 01:18:37.250
[Chris] No, Jaq.
Tell 'em they're too close!

01:18:37.416 --> 01:18:38.458
Pull back! Pull back!

01:18:38.625 --> 01:18:39.750
[Havelock] Not too close now.

01:18:41.041 --> 01:18:42.083
[SWAT 1] Target is boxed in.

01:18:42.250 --> 01:18:43.750
Aerial unit
is touching down...

01:18:43.916 --> 01:18:44.916
-Oh, shit!
-[tires screeching]

01:18:47.000 --> 01:18:48.333
Fall back! Fall back!

01:18:49.291 --> 01:18:50.375
Abort! Abort!

01:18:52.333 --> 01:18:54.041
No, no, no!

01:18:54.208 --> 01:18:56.125
All units,
this is Detective Jaq Diallo.

01:18:56.291 --> 01:18:57.250
As ranking officer,

01:18:57.416 --> 01:18:58.833
I'm taking over
incident command.

01:18:59.000 --> 01:19:01.000
If he clears the bridge,
he'll turn back to Mercy.

01:19:01.166 --> 01:19:02.875
Havelock,
send in the ordnance.

01:19:03.041 --> 01:19:04.125
Take him out.

01:19:04.291 --> 01:19:05.291
Wait, wait, wait.
No, no, no. What?

01:19:05.458 --> 01:19:06.375
If he gets that bomb back

01:19:06.541 --> 01:19:08.041
into a populated area,
he will destroy the...

01:19:08.208 --> 01:19:09.083
Britt is in the truck,

01:19:09.250 --> 01:19:10.125
and he's using her
as a shield!

01:19:10.291 --> 01:19:11.166
Chris, any other day

01:19:11.333 --> 01:19:12.791
you'd make the same call.
I'm sorry.

01:19:12.958 --> 01:19:14.541
Jaq, you gotta call
Havelock off. Jaq?

01:19:15.708 --> 01:19:17.083
No, no, no!

01:19:18.500 --> 01:19:19.500
Get me on with Havelock.

01:19:24.875 --> 01:19:26.208
You have a channel to him now.

01:19:26.375 --> 01:19:27.958
[Chris] Havelock,
it's Raven...

01:19:28.125 --> 01:19:29.125
he's got my daughter in there.

01:19:29.291 --> 01:19:30.833
I'm sorry, Detective.
I have my orders.

01:19:31.000 --> 01:19:32.166
[Chris] It's the wrong move.

01:19:32.333 --> 01:19:33.833
It's the wrong move
and you know it.

01:19:34.791 --> 01:19:36.291
[Jaq] Havelock, send it now.

01:19:36.458 --> 01:19:37.875
[Chris] No, no, no!

01:19:38.041 --> 01:19:39.291
Havelock, listen to me!

01:19:39.458 --> 01:19:41.125
We've got the smartest judge
in the world here.

01:19:41.291 --> 01:19:42.208
Let her make the call.

01:19:42.375 --> 01:19:43.333
[Maddox] If he approaches
at sufficient speed...

01:19:43.500 --> 01:19:44.750
everyone in this building

01:19:44.916 --> 01:19:46.250
and in the truck
will be killed.

01:19:46.416 --> 01:19:48.208
Please, Maddox. Maddox?

01:19:48.375 --> 01:19:49.375
[Maddox] No.

01:19:50.083 --> 01:19:51.250
Not Britt.

01:19:51.416 --> 01:19:53.458
Chris, I should not
interfere with this.

01:19:53.625 --> 01:19:55.041
Havelock, don't do it!

01:19:55.208 --> 01:19:57.458
-[whirring]
-[Chris grunts]

01:20:01.416 --> 01:20:02.791
-No!
-[beeps]

01:20:03.666 --> 01:20:05.000
[Chris panting]

01:20:07.291 --> 01:20:08.708
-Shit!
-Misfire, misfire.

01:20:08.875 --> 01:20:10.500
No detonation! No detonation!
Move out! Move out!

01:20:10.666 --> 01:20:13.625
No detonation! Clear out!
Clear out! Get in! Get in!

01:20:13.791 --> 01:20:15.000
[intense music playing]

01:20:19.041 --> 01:20:21.250
[Chris panting]

01:20:21.791 --> 01:20:23.083
Was that you?

01:20:23.791 --> 01:20:25.375
[Jaq] We're all
out of options.

01:20:25.541 --> 01:20:27.583
Chris, do you hear me?

01:20:28.208 --> 01:20:30.291
-[truck horn blaring]
-[people screaming]

01:20:31.541 --> 01:20:33.333
[Jaq] He's turning back
towards Mercy.

01:20:35.750 --> 01:20:36.833
[Jaq] He is
three minutes away.

01:20:37.000 --> 01:20:38.916
I'm gonna issue
an order to evacuate.

01:20:39.083 --> 01:20:40.750
[automated voice]
Please evacuate immediately.

01:20:40.916 --> 01:20:42.291
[people screaming]

01:20:42.458 --> 01:20:44.333
Please evacuate immediately.

01:20:44.500 --> 01:20:45.916
[guard] All teams, move in.

01:20:46.083 --> 01:20:47.625
[automated voice]
Please evacuate immediately.

01:20:48.333 --> 01:20:49.708
Please evacuate immediately.

01:20:49.875 --> 01:20:52.166
-[Chris] Jaq, I need you.
-For what?

01:20:52.333 --> 01:20:53.208
[Chris] We're gonna
try talking to him.

01:20:53.375 --> 01:20:54.541
Maddox, you with me?

01:20:54.708 --> 01:20:55.625
Detective Diallo,

01:20:55.791 --> 01:20:57.583
please put your air unit
in front of the truck.

01:20:57.750 --> 01:21:00.000
I require the driver's face
on your camera.

01:21:00.166 --> 01:21:01.833
Get as close as possible.

01:21:02.000 --> 01:21:03.000
[Jaq] Copy.

01:21:08.500 --> 01:21:10.250
[Maddox] You are now live
on the base radio channel

01:21:10.416 --> 01:21:11.500
he was listening to before.

01:21:11.666 --> 01:21:12.958
Rob? Rob, you hear me?

01:21:13.125 --> 01:21:14.625
-[Rob] Hey, holy shit.
-It's Chris.

01:21:14.791 --> 01:21:16.750
[Rob] You're not gonna
talk me down, Chris.

01:21:16.916 --> 01:21:17.916
-Dad, help! Help!
-[Chris] Rob...

01:21:18.083 --> 01:21:19.708
you can stop this.
You could let Britt go.

01:21:19.875 --> 01:21:21.458
When you walked
into that AA meeting...

01:21:21.625 --> 01:21:24.666
I knew exactly who you were.

01:21:24.833 --> 01:21:26.916
You had been haunting
my dreams, Chris.

01:21:27.083 --> 01:21:28.875
My brother had problems...

01:21:29.041 --> 01:21:30.208
but I coulda helped him.

01:21:30.375 --> 01:21:31.708
I coulda gotten him straight.

01:21:31.875 --> 01:21:33.166
You started
all of this, man...

01:21:33.333 --> 01:21:35.500
If it's about me
and the judge, why did you...

01:21:35.666 --> 01:21:37.041
I needed you in that chair.

01:21:37.208 --> 01:21:38.708
You had to suffer
in that chair,

01:21:38.875 --> 01:21:39.916
knowing that
you were innocent.

01:21:40.083 --> 01:21:42.166
-Same way that my brother did.
-Your brother was a murderer.

01:21:42.333 --> 01:21:43.458
-No, he wasn't!
-Don't listen to him, Dad!

01:21:43.625 --> 01:21:44.625
[Chris] If he wasn't,
how do you think

01:21:44.791 --> 01:21:45.750
that this helps him?

01:21:45.916 --> 01:21:46.791
You're killing people
in his name.

01:21:46.958 --> 01:21:47.791
Innocent people.

01:21:47.958 --> 01:21:49.125
You think that's gonna
set things right?

01:21:49.291 --> 01:21:51.583
[Rob] No, no, no. I tried.
I called. I spoke to...

01:21:51.750 --> 01:21:53.625
[Jaq] We can't let him
get away with this!

01:21:53.791 --> 01:21:55.500
[Rob] And she,
she told me that if I...

01:21:55.666 --> 01:21:57.208
-[Jaq] Shut your mouth!
-[Britt screaming]

01:21:57.375 --> 01:21:58.625
Jaq! Was that...
What are you doing?

01:21:58.791 --> 01:21:59.791
-[gunshots]
-[Rob] This is bullshit!

01:21:59.958 --> 01:22:01.541
What do you think?
I had a shot, and I took it.

01:22:01.708 --> 01:22:02.416
Britt is in the truck.

01:22:03.250 --> 01:22:04.208
-Are you nuts?
-[Jaq] I said stop!

01:22:05.041 --> 01:22:06.041
[Jaq grunts]

01:22:10.041 --> 01:22:11.666
Oh, Jesus. Oh, God!

01:22:13.375 --> 01:22:15.041
[people screaming]

01:22:17.458 --> 01:22:18.500
[panting]

01:22:25.833 --> 01:22:26.833
[Maddox] Power interrupted.

01:22:27.000 --> 01:22:29.000
-Backup battery activated.
-[Chris] Maddox!

01:22:29.166 --> 01:22:30.458
What the hell is happening?

01:22:30.625 --> 01:22:31.875
[Maddox] Systems operating

01:22:32.041 --> 01:22:34.708
-at 40% efficiency.
-[Britt screams]

01:22:35.250 --> 01:22:37.291
Get me out of here! Maddox!

01:22:37.458 --> 01:22:38.333
[Britt screams]

01:22:38.500 --> 01:22:39.458
-[Maddox] Systems operating...
-[Britt] Dad!

01:22:39.625 --> 01:22:40.625
...at 40% efficiency.

01:22:40.791 --> 01:22:41.625
-Britt.
-[Maddox] Efficiency.

01:22:41.791 --> 01:22:43.000
-[Chris] Maddox!
-Efficiency.

01:22:43.166 --> 01:22:44.625
End the trial.
I have to get out there!

01:22:44.791 --> 01:22:45.916
[officer] Move! Move!

01:22:46.583 --> 01:22:47.583
[gunshot]

01:22:49.541 --> 01:22:50.500
[Chris straining]

01:22:53.500 --> 01:22:54.666
This is
the Mercy Capital Court.

01:22:54.833 --> 01:22:55.541
I'm Judge Maddox,

01:22:55.708 --> 01:22:56.458
and I'm going
to preside over your...

01:22:56.625 --> 01:22:58.625
Maddox! Maddox, end the trial.

01:22:58.791 --> 01:23:00.666
I'm programmed
to remain online

01:23:00.833 --> 01:23:02.625
until I stop
the trial recording.

01:23:02.791 --> 01:23:04.791
And I still have
internal network access.

01:23:05.416 --> 01:23:07.458
Christopher Raven
to the lobby.

01:23:07.625 --> 01:23:08.833
Christopher Raven, you are...

01:23:09.000 --> 01:23:11.208
-Maddox! End the trial!
-...wanted in the lobby.

01:23:13.250 --> 01:23:14.250
Now.

01:23:15.125 --> 01:23:16.125
Maddox!

01:23:19.583 --> 01:23:21.208
I will assist you
however I can.

01:23:21.375 --> 01:23:22.791
[panting]

01:23:25.291 --> 01:23:27.458
[officer] Please evacuate
the building.

01:23:27.625 --> 01:23:29.625
[automated voice]
Please evacuate immediately.

01:23:29.791 --> 01:23:31.166
Please evacuate immediately.

01:23:31.333 --> 01:23:33.541
[officer] Evacuate
the building quickly!

01:23:33.708 --> 01:23:35.333
[automated voice]
Please evacuate immediately.

01:23:37.000 --> 01:23:38.083
[negotiator] Rob Nelson,

01:23:38.250 --> 01:23:40.791
this is the LAPD
hostage negotiating team.

01:23:42.083 --> 01:23:43.666
Come on. Talk to me, Rob.

01:23:44.333 --> 01:23:45.875
No need for anybody
to get hurt here.

01:23:46.041 --> 01:23:47.333
Chris!

01:23:47.500 --> 01:23:49.833
-You got me, Maddox?
-[Maddox] Yep, I have you.

01:23:50.000 --> 01:23:51.208
[negotiator] We know
you have Britt Raven in there.

01:23:51.375 --> 01:23:53.000
-Bring her on out, Rob.
-You got a visitor.

01:23:53.166 --> 01:23:54.541
[Chris] Can't do this, Rob!

01:23:54.708 --> 01:23:56.125
About two years
I've been planning this!

01:23:56.291 --> 01:23:57.625
[Chris] Okay, wait.

01:23:57.791 --> 01:23:58.875
Two years since you
put an innocent man

01:23:59.041 --> 01:24:00.166
to death in that chair...

01:24:00.333 --> 01:24:01.708
[Chris] He wants to think
that his brother

01:24:01.875 --> 01:24:03.208
was not a murderer, so...

01:24:03.375 --> 01:24:05.166
give him an opportunity
to try to prove it...

01:24:05.333 --> 01:24:07.208
and buy me some time
to figure a way out of this.

01:24:07.375 --> 01:24:09.000
[Maddox] If I commence
an official court hearing...

01:24:09.166 --> 01:24:09.916
to take his testimony

01:24:10.083 --> 01:24:11.166
-on the record...
-Chris!

01:24:11.333 --> 01:24:13.916
...I can bypass the firewall
and restore cloud access.

01:24:14.083 --> 01:24:15.250
All right. Do it.

01:24:15.416 --> 01:24:16.416
[negotiator] Nelson,
put the gun down.

01:24:16.583 --> 01:24:18.083
-Chris, get out here! Now!
-[gunshots]

01:24:18.250 --> 01:24:19.291
-[Britt] Dad!
-Okay!

01:24:19.875 --> 01:24:21.416
-Dad! Please.
-[Chris] It's okay!

01:24:21.750 --> 01:24:24.000
It's okay! It's okay, kiddo.

01:24:24.166 --> 01:24:25.875
I'm not gonna let anything
happen to you.

01:24:26.041 --> 01:24:27.166
Let her go, Rob.

01:24:27.333 --> 01:24:28.541
You can do anything
you want to me,

01:24:28.708 --> 01:24:30.041
just... just let her go.

01:24:31.250 --> 01:24:33.333
You said that
Nic was necessary.

01:24:33.500 --> 01:24:35.000
Britt is not. You know it.

01:24:35.166 --> 01:24:37.000
Shut up! It ends here.

01:24:37.166 --> 01:24:40.500
You, the judge, this place,
and everything it stands for.

01:24:40.666 --> 01:24:42.958
-Dad, he's got a bomb.
-No, he doesn't.

01:24:43.500 --> 01:24:45.083
That bomb was working,
he'd have blown it.

01:24:45.250 --> 01:24:46.416
He's just an angry man
with a gun.

01:24:47.708 --> 01:24:51.416
What makes you think
that it's not workin'?

01:24:51.583 --> 01:24:52.958
-[beeping]
-Dead-man switch.

01:24:53.416 --> 01:24:54.333
Did you think
I was really gonna

01:24:54.500 --> 01:24:55.666
blow this thing
before I made sure...

01:24:55.833 --> 01:24:57.166
that you were
still in the building?

01:24:58.083 --> 01:24:59.333
So, here's my verdict.

01:24:59.500 --> 01:25:02.083
You're guilty of executing
an innocent man.

01:25:03.083 --> 01:25:04.083
It's over.

01:25:04.583 --> 01:25:06.041
-No, no, no!
-[rapid beeping]

01:25:06.416 --> 01:25:08.541
Mr. Nelson, I'm Judge Maddox.

01:25:09.208 --> 01:25:10.875
You claim
your brother was innocent?

01:25:11.708 --> 01:25:13.125
Before you destroy me
and this court

01:25:13.291 --> 01:25:14.250
I suggest that...

01:25:14.416 --> 01:25:15.291
-you put your case...
-What?

01:25:15.458 --> 01:25:16.416
...on the record.

01:25:16.583 --> 01:25:19.083
This is a chance for you
to clear your brother's name.

01:25:19.250 --> 01:25:20.541
If you believe you can.

01:25:20.708 --> 01:25:22.458
Of course, I can!
That's the point.

01:25:22.625 --> 01:25:25.333
Then I, hereby, declare this
addendum evidence hearing...

01:25:25.500 --> 01:25:27.791
in the trial of David Webb...
open.

01:25:28.666 --> 01:25:29.875
Okay.

01:25:31.000 --> 01:25:34.083
In that case, please. Proceed.

01:25:34.541 --> 01:25:36.791
About two years ago,
I found him.

01:25:36.958 --> 01:25:40.750
June 15th, Third and Hobart,
about four in the afternoon.

01:25:40.916 --> 01:25:42.416
He was... all full of shame...

01:25:42.583 --> 01:25:44.333
high out of his mind.
I was all shook up.

01:25:45.375 --> 01:25:48.916
I gave him some cash and then
I gave him a phone so that...

01:25:49.083 --> 01:25:51.958
I could call him
when I came up with a plan.

01:25:52.125 --> 01:25:53.333
Next thing I know,

01:25:53.500 --> 01:25:54.791
you're saying
he killed this lady.

01:25:54.958 --> 01:25:56.041
But here's the thing,
I called him

01:25:56.208 --> 01:25:57.833
the night of the murder!

01:25:58.291 --> 01:26:00.375
Same time you said
he was killin' that lady...

01:26:00.541 --> 01:26:01.875
I was talking to him!

01:26:02.041 --> 01:26:03.125
-His detonator appears to...
-Okay?

01:26:03.291 --> 01:26:04.291
...lack any arming mechanism.

01:26:04.458 --> 01:26:05.250
[Rob] Go on back and check
my cell phone records.

01:26:05.416 --> 01:26:06.250
[Rob] I know you got 'em.

01:26:06.416 --> 01:26:07.291
[Maddox] There's an 82%
chance that...

01:26:07.458 --> 01:26:08.291
...pulling the battery pack...

01:26:08.458 --> 01:26:09.375
-[Rob] Are you even listening?
-...will render it inert

01:26:09.541 --> 01:26:11.208
-without detonation.
-You are not listening to me!

01:26:11.375 --> 01:26:12.291
I am listening very closely,

01:26:12.458 --> 01:26:14.125
-Mr. Nelson.
-No.

01:26:14.291 --> 01:26:15.208
The body of Valerie Bennett

01:26:15.375 --> 01:26:18.041
was found in an underpass
at 6:00 a.m.

01:26:18.208 --> 01:26:20.625
She had been stabbed to death
at approximately 10:00 p.m.

01:26:20.791 --> 01:26:22.208
-the night before.
-[mouthing]

01:26:22.375 --> 01:26:24.166
[Maddox] Your brother
was found with her body...

01:26:24.333 --> 01:26:25.833
with his prints
on the knife...

01:26:26.000 --> 01:26:27.541
and he did not have a phone.

01:26:27.708 --> 01:26:28.791
[Rob] No, I just told you.

01:26:28.958 --> 01:26:31.333
I was on the phone with him
at 10:00 p.m.

01:26:31.500 --> 01:26:33.250
We talked for over an hour!

01:26:33.416 --> 01:26:34.833
You do not care
about the truth!

01:26:35.000 --> 01:26:37.791
You are just a heartless
killing machine!

01:26:37.958 --> 01:26:39.458
This place
is just a slaughterhouse!

01:26:39.625 --> 01:26:40.625
[Maddox] I'm sorry,
Mr. Nelson.

01:26:40.791 --> 01:26:41.583
Your evidence has failed

01:26:41.750 --> 01:26:43.458
to reduce
the probability of guilt...

01:26:43.625 --> 01:26:46.000
that led to
your brother's execution.

01:26:46.541 --> 01:26:48.291
-[Rob screams]
-Britt!

01:26:48.708 --> 01:26:49.583
-[Rob] No!
-[Chris grunts]

01:26:49.750 --> 01:26:51.166
[rapid beeping]

01:26:51.916 --> 01:26:53.416
-[both grunting]
-Dad!

01:26:57.833 --> 01:26:58.750
-[gunshots]
-[screams]

01:26:59.875 --> 01:27:00.916
-[both straining]
-[beeping continues]

01:27:01.458 --> 01:27:02.416
[beeping stops]

01:27:10.708 --> 01:27:11.750
[Chris yells]

01:27:11.916 --> 01:27:12.958
[groaning]

01:27:15.041 --> 01:27:16.041
On your knees!

01:27:16.291 --> 01:27:17.291
Turn around!

01:27:18.000 --> 01:27:20.125
Chris! No. Don't.

01:27:20.291 --> 01:27:21.416
He murdered Nic!

01:27:21.750 --> 01:27:22.750
He's gonna pay.

01:27:22.916 --> 01:27:24.291
Now, get up!

01:27:27.333 --> 01:27:28.458
This doesn't fix anything.

01:27:28.625 --> 01:27:31.208
-Shut your mouth.
-[Britt] Dad, don't!

01:27:31.375 --> 01:27:32.375
Please.

01:27:33.500 --> 01:27:34.583
[intense music playing]

01:27:36.125 --> 01:27:37.125
[straining]

01:27:37.875 --> 01:27:38.958
Dad!

01:27:40.083 --> 01:27:41.250
[yelling]

01:27:42.416 --> 01:27:43.458
Dad!

01:27:45.500 --> 01:27:47.833
I was on the phone with him
the whole time, Chris.

01:27:48.000 --> 01:27:49.333
I called your precinct.

01:27:49.500 --> 01:27:50.333
-[gunshots]
-[Rob grunts]

01:27:53.041 --> 01:27:54.458
[Chris] No, Jaq.
Not now! Nope!

01:27:54.625 --> 01:27:56.041
-Let me finish this.
-No, Jaq!

01:27:56.208 --> 01:27:57.500
Hey! Hey!

01:27:58.291 --> 01:27:59.291
[officer] Back up. Okay.

01:27:59.458 --> 01:28:01.666
-We're okay.
-[Rob] I called the station.

01:28:01.833 --> 01:28:04.416
I spoke to some lady,
and she told me...

01:28:04.583 --> 01:28:08.125
that she would give me
a call back as soon... God!

01:28:08.541 --> 01:28:10.166
[Chris] Maddox, verify.

01:28:10.750 --> 01:28:12.416
It was July 15th.

01:28:15.375 --> 01:28:16.416
-[David] Hello?
-[Rob] Hey, buddy, it's me.

01:28:16.583 --> 01:28:17.583
It's Rob.

01:28:17.750 --> 01:28:18.666
[David] Do you think
I can maybe crash

01:28:18.833 --> 01:28:19.833
at your place for a while...

01:28:20.000 --> 01:28:21.208
just till I get back
on my feet?

01:28:21.375 --> 01:28:23.125
[Rob] Of course.
Anything you need.

01:28:23.291 --> 01:28:24.291
I'm always here for you.

01:28:24.458 --> 01:28:26.458
[Rob] I told a woman
at the precinct

01:28:26.625 --> 01:28:28.541
to check my call history!

01:28:28.708 --> 01:28:30.666
Whoever booked him
knows what happened.

01:28:30.833 --> 01:28:32.375
[Chris] Wait...

01:28:32.541 --> 01:28:34.291
do you know if someone
called about an alibi?

01:28:36.583 --> 01:28:37.625
Did you know?

01:28:37.791 --> 01:28:38.750
[Rob] I was trying
to get through

01:28:38.916 --> 01:28:40.083
to someone the whole time!

01:28:40.250 --> 01:28:41.416
No one would listen!

01:28:42.833 --> 01:28:45.208
You processed Webb.
Did he have a cell phone?

01:28:46.041 --> 01:28:47.041
-Jaq?
-[Jaq] Stop.

01:28:47.416 --> 01:28:49.458
-You need to hear me, Chris.
-[Chris] You took him in, Jaq.

01:28:49.625 --> 01:28:51.375
I have tracked the cell phone.

01:28:51.541 --> 01:28:54.083
It was at the scene
when David Webb was arrested.

01:28:54.250 --> 01:28:55.666
Then at the station.

01:28:56.375 --> 01:28:58.000
[Chris] Maddox,
bypass the LAPD firewall

01:28:58.166 --> 01:28:59.541
with my login.

01:29:01.208 --> 01:29:02.208
[Jaq] Don't do this.

01:29:02.375 --> 01:29:04.208
[Chris] Check
the evidence room.

01:29:04.375 --> 01:29:05.666
And show me Jaq's bodycam.

01:29:12.083 --> 01:29:13.291
[Maddox] Phone tracking
records show

01:29:13.416 --> 01:29:15.708
the phone in the evidence room
at this time.

01:29:15.875 --> 01:29:17.500
But it wasn't processed.

01:29:17.666 --> 01:29:18.833
[Chris] Why is it missing,
Jaq?

01:29:23.791 --> 01:29:25.958
Did you drive straight home
that night, Jaq,

01:29:26.125 --> 01:29:27.250
or should we check?

01:29:27.708 --> 01:29:28.708
Maddox?

01:29:46.291 --> 01:29:48.125
You buried the phone.

01:29:48.666 --> 01:29:50.708
We needed the first trial
to be a home run.

01:29:51.958 --> 01:29:53.500
We need Mercy, Chris.

01:29:54.875 --> 01:29:56.750
We need these scumbags scared.

01:29:56.916 --> 01:29:58.375
Look at what it's done for us.

01:29:59.375 --> 01:30:02.208
You'd destroy it all
if this gets out.

01:30:03.291 --> 01:30:04.750
We need justice, Jaq.

01:30:05.958 --> 01:30:07.166
Not this.

01:30:14.166 --> 01:30:15.916
Detain Detective Diallo
and Robert Nelson.

01:30:16.083 --> 01:30:16.958
[officer 2] Let's go.

01:30:17.125 --> 01:30:18.083
[officer 3] Let's move on out,
guys.

01:30:18.250 --> 01:30:19.708
Get up. On your feet.

01:30:19.875 --> 01:30:22.583
-[Britt] Dad.
-Britt, hey. Hey.

01:30:22.750 --> 01:30:24.958
You're okay. You're okay.

01:30:25.125 --> 01:30:26.708
-Hey, are you hurt?
-No.

01:30:26.875 --> 01:30:29.250
-Are you sure?
-Yeah. I'm okay.

01:30:31.208 --> 01:30:32.666
I'm sorry, Dad.

01:30:33.458 --> 01:30:35.291
I'm sorry I ever thought
you could hurt Mom.

01:30:35.458 --> 01:30:36.958
I got you. I got you.

01:30:38.166 --> 01:30:39.708
I'm not going anywhere.

01:30:41.541 --> 01:30:43.041
[somber music playing]

01:30:49.541 --> 01:30:50.541
[Maddox] Chris...

01:30:54.458 --> 01:30:56.166
What have we done?

01:30:58.750 --> 01:31:00.416
We just did what
we're programmed to do.

01:31:02.666 --> 01:31:05.000
Human or AI.

01:31:07.458 --> 01:31:08.875
We all make mistakes...

01:31:11.458 --> 01:31:13.291
and we learn.

01:31:18.541 --> 01:31:20.000
Yes, we do.

01:31:26.083 --> 01:31:27.083
[exhales]

01:31:27.625 --> 01:31:28.625
Maddox?

01:31:37.000 --> 01:31:39.000
[dramatic music playing]

01:31:56.000 --> 01:31:57.416
[slow electronic song playing]

01:34:45.666 --> 01:34:47.291
[intriguing music playing]
